-- | Public interface for the various prelude modules
module frege.Prelude

-- | Print a value to the standard output writer. 
--   This will come out UTF8 encoded.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#print
print ∷ Show α ⇒ α → IO ()

-- | Print a value to the standard output stream and append a platform typical new line character. 
--   This will come out UTF8 encoded.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#println
println ∷ Show α ⇒ α → IO ()

-- | write a character to <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/./java/IO.html#stdout" >IO.stdout</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#putChar
putChar ∷ Char → IO ()

-- | write a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/./prelude/PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> to standard output (Haskell compatibility)
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#putStr
putStr ∷ String → IO ()

-- | write a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/./prelude/PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> and a new line to standard output (Haskell compatibility)
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#putStrLn
putStrLn ∷ String → IO ()

-- | read a character from the standard input reader
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#getChar
getChar ∷ IO Char

-- | read a line from the standard input reader, end of line characters are removed.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#getLine
getLine ∷ IO String

-- | The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#getContents" >getContents</a> operation returns all user input as a single string
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#getContents
getContents ∷ IO String

-- | The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#getContentsOf" >getContentsOf</a> operation returns all input from the supplied <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/./java/IO.html#Reader" >Reader</a> as a single string. 
--   After completion, the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/./java/IO.html#Reader" >Reader</a> is closed.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#getContentsOf
getContentsOf ∷ Reader → IO String

-- | The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#interact" >interact</a> function takes a function of type <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/./prelude/PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> -> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/./prelude/PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> as its argument. The entire input from the standard input device is passed to this function as its argument, and the resulting string is output on the standard output device.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#interact
interact ∷ (String→String) → IO ()

-- | The readFile function reads a file and returns the contents of the file as a string. 
--   If the file doesn't exist, a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/./java/IO.html#FileNotFoundException" >FileNotFoundException</a> will be thrown.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#readFile
readFile ∷ String → IO String

-- | Writes the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/./prelude/PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> given as second argument to the file whose name is given as the first argument. 
--   After completion, the file will be closed.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#writeFile
writeFile ∷ String → String → IO ()

-- | Appends the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/./prelude/PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> given as second argument to the file whose name is given as the first argument. 
--   After completion, the file will be closed.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#appendFile
appendFile ∷ String → String → IO ()

-- | unsafe trace, returns always <b >false</b> and can thus be used like 
--  <pre>
--  
--   fun x y
--      | trace   (&quot;x is &quot; ++ show x) = undefined
--      | traceLn (&quot;y is &quot; ++ show y) = undefined
--      | otherwise = ......
--  </pre> 
--   Note that this imposes strictness on the traced data.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#trace
trace ∷ String → Bool

-- | same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#trace" >trace</a> but appends a line break
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/Prelude#traceLn
traceLn ∷ String → Bool

-- | type class for <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Arrow#Arrow" >Arrow</a>s
module frege.control.Arrow

-- | Basic arrow definitions, based on Generalising Monads to Arrows, by John Hughes, Science of Computer Programming, pp67-111, May 2000. <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Arrow#Arrow__minus_gt" >-></a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Arrow.arr" >arr</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Arrow#Arrow" >Arrow</a> a ⇒ (b → c) → a b c</span> 
--   
--   Lift a function to an arrow.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Arrow#Arrow
class (Semigroupoid.Semigroupoid a, Tensor.Tensor a, Second a, First a, CombineIn a, Category a) ⇒ Arrow a

-- | Lift a function to an arrow.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Arrow#Arrow.arr
arr ∷ Arrow a ⇒ (b → c) → a b c

-- | Introduction of the type class for <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category_(mathematics)" >categories</a>.
module frege.control.Category

-- | A category is a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/./Semigroupoid.html#Semigroupoid" >Semigroupoid</a> with the following additional properties: <ul > <li > For every object <span class="code" >A</span>, there exists a mophism <span class="code" >id(A): A -> A</span> called the <i >identity morphism for A</i>, such that for every morphism <span class="code" >f: A -> B</span> we have</li> </ul> 
--  <pre>
--  
--   id(B) &bull; f = f = f &bull; id(A)
--  </pre> <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Category#Category__minus_gt" >-></a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Category.id" >id</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Category#Category" >Category</a> f ⇒ f a a</span> 
--   
--   the identity morphism
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Category#Category
class Semigroupoid f ⇒ Category f

-- | the identity morphism
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Category#Category.id
id ∷ Category f ⇒ f a a

-- | type class <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/CombineIn#CombineIn" >CombineIn</a>, which provides the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/CombineIn#CombineIn._amp_amp_amp" >CombineIn.&&&</a> operator
module frege.control.CombineIn

-- | <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/CombineIn#CombineIn__minus_gt" >-></a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="CombineIn._amp_amp_amp" >&&&</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/CombineIn#CombineIn" >CombineIn</a> f ⇒ f a b → f a c → f a (b, c)<br ></br>
--  <b >infixr</b>  3</span> 
--   
--   Send the input to both argument semigroupoids and combine their output.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/CombineIn#CombineIn
class Semigroupoid f ⇒ CombineIn f

-- | Send the input to both argument semigroupoids and combine their output.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/CombineIn#CombineIn._amp_amp_amp
(&&&) ∷  CombineIn f ⇒ f a b → f a c → f a (b, c) 
infixr  3

-- | Support for concurrency.
--   Concurrency in Frege comes in 2 flavors. The first is through <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../java/Lang.html#Thread" >Thread</a>s, which are, unlike in Haskell, <i >OS threads</i>.
--   The second possibility is to use a thread pool and an executor service one can submit tasks to. But note that blocking asynchronous tasks, unlike Haskell green threads, will block an OS thread on blocking actions.
module frege.control.Concurrent

-- | A thread safe, shared variable, that is either full or empty. 
--   Technically, this is just a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../java/util/Concurrent.html#BlockingQueue" >BlockingQueue</a> restricted to length 1.  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><b >private</b> <a name="MVar.MV" >MV</a> (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../java/util/Concurrent.html#BlockingQueue" >BlockingQueue</a> a)</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MVar._new" >new</a> ∷ α → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a> α)</span> 
--   
--   create a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a> filled with a value   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MVar.newEmpty" >newEmpty</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a> α)</span> 
--   
--   create an empty <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a>   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MVar.offer" >offer</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a> α</b> → <b >α</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a></span> 
--   
--   put a value in a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a>, returns false if already full.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MVar.poll" >poll</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a> α</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Maybe" >Maybe</a> α)</span> 
--   
--   get the value from a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a>, return <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Maybe.Nothing" >Maybe.Nothing</a> when empty   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MVar.put" >put</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a> α</b> → <b >α</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Unit" >()</a></span> 
--   
--   put a value in a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a>, blocks if full   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MVar.take" >take</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a> α</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> α</span> 
--   
--   take a value from a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a>, blocks if empty
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar
data MVar a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar.MV
private MV (BlockingQueue a)

-- | Alias for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar.newEmpty" >MVar.newEmpty</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#newEmptyMVar
newEmptyMVar ∷ IO (MVar α)

-- | Alias for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar._new" >MVar.new</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#newMVar
newMVar ∷ α → IO (MVar α)

-- | Alias for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar.take" >MVar.take</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#takeMVar
takeMVar ∷ MVar α → IO α

-- | Alias for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar.put" >MVar.put</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#putMVar
putMVar ∷ MVar α → α → IO ()

-- | Alias for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar.poll" >MVar.poll</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#tryTakeMVar
tryTakeMVar ∷ MVar α → IO (Maybe α)

-- | Alias for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar.offer" >MVar.offer</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#tryPutMVar
tryPutMVar ∷ MVar α → α → IO Bool

-- | Create and start a new OS <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../java/Lang.html#Thread" >Thread</a> that runs an <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> action.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#forkOS
forkOS ∷ IO () → IO Thread

-- | Run the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> action asynchronously in an <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../java/util/Concurrent.html#ExecutorService" >ExecutorService</a> 
--   This is not suitable for not-ending processes! 
--   The executor service may manage a fixed small number of concurrent threads only.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#forkIO
forkIO ∷ IO () → IO ()

-- | Shutdwon the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../java/util/Concurrent.html#ExecutorService" >ExecutorService</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#shutdown
shutdown ∷ IO ()

-- | Run a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> action asynchronously and return the result in a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#MVar" >MVar</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Concurrent#async
async ∷ IO a → IO (MVar (Exception | a))

-- | type class <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/First#First" >First</a> with <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/First#First.first" >First.first</a> operation
module frege.control.First

-- | <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/First#First__minus_gt" >-></a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="First.first" >first</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/First#First" >First</a> f ⇒ f a b → f (a, c) (b, c)</span> 
--   
--   Send the first component of the input through the argument tensor, and copy the rest unchanged to the output.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/First#First
class (Semigroupoid.Semigroupoid f, Tensor f) ⇒ First f

-- | Send the first component of the input through the argument tensor, and copy the rest unchanged to the output.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/First#First.first
first ∷ First f ⇒ f a b → f (a, c) (b, c)

-- | type class <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Second#Second" >Second</a> with <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Second#Second.second" >Second.second</a> operation
module frege.control.Second

-- | <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Second#Second__minus_gt" >-></a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Second.second" >second</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Second#Second" >Second</a> f ⇒ f c d → f (a, c) (a, d)</span> 
--   
--   Send the second component of the input through the argument tensor, and copy the rest unchanged to the output.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Second#Second
class (Semigroupoid.Semigroupoid f, Tensor f) ⇒ Second f

-- | Send the second component of the input through the argument tensor, and copy the rest unchanged to the output.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Second#Second.second
second ∷ Second f ⇒ f c d → f (a, c) (a, d)

-- | Introduction of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Semigroupoid" >semigroupoid</a>.
module frege.control.Semigroupoid

-- | Formally, a semigroupoid consists of <ul > <li > a set of things called objects. </li> <li > for every two objects A and B a set Mor(A,B) of things called morphisms from A to B. If <span class="code" >f</span> is in Mor(A,B), we write <span class="code" >f : A → B</span>.</li> <li > for every three objects A, B and C a binary operation <span class="code" >Mor(A,B) × Mor(B,C) → Mor(A,C)</span> called <b >composition</b> of morphisms. The composition of <span class="code" >f : A → B</span> and <span class="code" >g : B → C</span> is written as <span class="code" >g • f</span>.</li> </ul> 
--   such that the following axiom holds:  
--   associativity 
--   <div > if <span class="code" >f : A → B</span>, <span class="code" >g : B → C</span> and <span class="code" >h : C → D</span> then <span class="code" >h • (g • f) = (h • g) • f</span>. </div>   <ul > <li > </li> </ul> <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Semigroupoid#Semigroupoid__minus_gt" >-></a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Semigroupoid._bullet" >•</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Semigroupoid#Semigroupoid" >Semigroupoid</a> f ⇒ f b c → f a b → f a c<br ></br>
--  <b >infixr</b>  16</span> 
--   
--   morphism composition
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Semigroupoid#Semigroupoid
class Semigroupoid f

-- | morphism composition
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Semigroupoid#Semigroupoid._bullet
(•) ∷  Semigroupoid f ⇒ f b c → f a b → f a c 
infixr  16

-- | Right-to-left composition. This is the same a ordinary composition with <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Semigroupoid#Semigroupoid._bullet" >Semigroupoid.•</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Semigroupoid#_lt_lt_lt
(<<<) ∷  Semigroupoid f ⇒ f b c → f a b → f a c 
infixr  1

-- | Left-to-right composition
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Semigroupoid#_gt_gt_gt
(>>>) ∷  Semigroupoid f ⇒ f a b → f b c → f a c 
infixr  1

-- | The <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Tensor#Tensor" >Tensor</a> type class with <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Tensor#Tensor._star_star_star" >Tensor.***</a> operation.
module frege.control.Tensor

-- | <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Tensor#Tensor__minus_gt" >-></a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Tensor._star_star_star" >***</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Tensor#Tensor" >Tensor</a> f ⇒ f a b → f c d → f (a, c) (b, d)<br ></br>
--  <b >infixr</b>  3</span> 
--   
--   Split the input between the two argument semigroupoids and combine their output. Note that this is in general not a functor.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Tensor#Tensor
class Semigroupoid f ⇒ Tensor f

-- | Split the input between the two argument semigroupoids and combine their output. Note that this is in general not a functor.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/Tensor#Tensor._star_star_star
(***) ∷  Tensor f ⇒ f a b → f c d → f (a, c) (b, d) 
infixr  3

-- | Kleisli oprators, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/arrow/../Arrow.html#Arrow" >Arrow</a> and <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/arrow/../../prelude/PreludeMonad.html#Monad" >Monad</a> instances
module frege.control.arrow.Kleisli

-- | <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Kleisli.Kleisli" >Kleisli</a> {run ∷ a → m b}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Kleisli.run" >run</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/arrow/Kleisli#Kleisli" >Kleisli</a> α γ β</b> → γ → α β</span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >run</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/arrow/Kleisli#Kleisli
data Kleisli m a b

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/arrow/Kleisli#Kleisli.Kleisli
Kleisli {run ∷ a → m b}

-- | <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/Reader#Reader" >Reader</a> monad and monad transformer, based on <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/../arrow/Kleisli.html#Kleisli" >Kleisli</a>
module frege.control.monad.Reader

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/Reader#Reader
type Reader a b = Kleisli Identity a b

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/Reader#ReaderT
type ReaderT m a b = Kleisli m a b

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/Reader#ask
ask ∷ Monad m ⇒ ReaderT m e e

-- | The strict <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#State" >State</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/../../prelude/PreludeMonad.html#Monad" >Monad</a>
module frege.control.monad.State

-- | <span class="code" >State s a</span> is an abstract data type that resembles a stateful computation with State <i >s</i> and result <i >a</i>, i.e. functions of type <span class="code" >s -> (a, s)</span> where the State is immutable. <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><b >private</b> <a name="State.State" >State</a> (s → (a, s))</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="State.get" >get</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#State" >State</a> α α</span> 
--   
--   return the state from the internals of the monad   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="State.modify" >modify</a> ∷ (α→α) → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#State" >State</a> α <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Unit" >()</a></span> 
--   
--   modify the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#State" >State</a>   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="State.put" >put</a> ∷ α → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#State" >State</a> α <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Unit" >()</a></span> 
--   
--   replace the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#State" >State</a> inside the monad   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="State.run" >run</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#State" >State</a> α β</b> → α → (β, α)</span> 
--   
--   run a stateful computation
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#State
data State s a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#State.State
private State (s → (a, s))

-- | Alias for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#State.run" >State.run</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#runState
runState ∷ State α β → α → (β, α)

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#evalState
evalState ∷ State β α → β → α

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#execState
execState ∷ State α β → α → α

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#runStateT
runStateT ∷ Monad m ⇒ StateT s m v → s → m (v, s)

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#evalStateT
evalStateT ∷ Monad m ⇒ StateT s m v → s → m v

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#execStateT
execStateT ∷ Monad m ⇒ StateT s m v → s → m s

-- | <pre>
--  
--   StateT s m a
--  </pre> 
--   A stateful computation that transforms an inner <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/../../prelude/PreludeMonad.html#Monad" >Monad</a> <i >m</i>  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><b >private</b> <a name="StateT.StateT" >StateT</a> {run ∷ s → m (a, s)}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StateT.get" >get</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/../../prelude/PreludeMonad.html#Monad" >Monad</a> α ⇒ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#StateT" >StateT</a> β α β</span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StateT.modify" >modify</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/../../prelude/PreludeMonad.html#Monad" >Monad</a> α ⇒ (β→β) → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#StateT" >StateT</a> β α <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Unit" >()</a></span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StateT.put" >put</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/../../prelude/PreludeMonad.html#Monad" >Monad</a> α ⇒ β → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#StateT" >StateT</a> β α <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Unit" >()</a></span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StateT.run" >run</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#StateT" >StateT</a> γ α β</b> → γ → α (β, γ)</span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >run</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#StateT
data StateT s m a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#StateT.StateT
private StateT {run ∷ s → m (a, s)}

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/State#promote
promote ∷ Monad β ⇒ State α γ → StateT α β γ

module frege.control.monad.trans.EitherT

-- | <h3 > Constructors</h3>

--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>

-- | <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeMonad.html#Monad" >Monad</a> transformer for <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Maybe" >Maybe</a>
module frege.control.monad.trans.MaybeT

-- | The parameterizable maybe monad, obtained by composing an arbitrary monad with the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Maybe" >Maybe</a> monad. 
--   Computations are actions that may produce a value or fail. 
--   The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeMonad.html#Monad._return" >Monad.return</a> function yields a successful computation, while (>>=) sequences two subcomputations, failing on the first error. <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MaybeT.MaybeT" >MaybeT</a> {run ∷ m (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Maybe" >Maybe</a> a)}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MaybeT.run" >run</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MaybeT#MaybeT" >MaybeT</a> α β</b> → α (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Maybe" >Maybe</a> β)</span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >run</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MaybeT#MaybeT
data MaybeT m a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MaybeT#MaybeT.MaybeT
MaybeT {run ∷ m (Maybe a)}

-- | Transform the computation inside a <span class="code" >MaybeT</span>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MaybeT#mapMaybeT
mapMaybeT ∷ (m (Maybe a) → n (Maybe b)) → MaybeT m a → MaybeT n b

-- | Monads in which <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> computations may be embedded.
module frege.control.monad.trans.MonadIO

-- | Monads in which <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> computations may be embedded. 
--   Any monad built by applying a sequence of monad transformers to the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> monad will be an instance of this class. 
--   Instances should satisfy the following laws, which state that <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MonadIO#MonadIO.liftIO" >MonadIO.liftIO</a> is a transformer of monads: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   liftIO . return = return
--  </pre> 
--  <pre>
--  
--   liftIO (m &gt;&gt;= f) = liftIO m &gt;&gt;= (liftIO .  f)
--  </pre> <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MonadIO#MonadIO_IO" >ST</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MonadIO.liftIO" >liftIO</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MonadIO#MonadIO" >MonadIO</a> m ⇒ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> a → m a</span> 
--   
--   Lift a computation from the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> monad.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MonadIO#MonadIO
class (Functor m, Apply m, Bind m, Applicative m, Monad m) ⇒ MonadIO m

-- | Lift a computation from the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> monad.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MonadIO#MonadIO.liftIO
liftIO ∷ MonadIO m ⇒ IO a → m a

-- | provide utility function <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MonadTrans#MonadTrans.lift" >MonadTrans.lift</a> for <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeMonad.html#Monad" >Monad</a> transformers
module frege.control.monad.trans.MonadTrans

-- | <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MonadTrans.lift" >lift</a> ∷ (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MonadTrans#MonadTrans" >MonadTrans</a> t, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/../../../prelude/PreludeMonad.html#Monad" >Monad</a> m) ⇒ m a → t m a</span> 
--   
--   Lift a computation from the argument monad to the constructed monad.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MonadTrans#MonadTrans
class MonadTrans t

-- | Lift a computation from the argument monad to the constructed monad.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/control/monad/trans/MonadTrans#MonadTrans.lift
lift ∷ (MonadTrans t, Monad m) ⇒ m a → t m a

-- | Fast sets for small integers and enumerations, implemented as bit operations on <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Long" >Long</a> There may be at most 64 elements, due to the bit size of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Long" >Long</a>.
module frege.data.Bits

-- | <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="BitSet.BitSet" >BitSet</a> {set ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Long" >Long</a>}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="BitSet.difference" >difference</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a> α</b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a> α</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a> α</span> 
--   
--   <span class="code" >a `difference` b</span> -- a set with all elements that are members of a and not members of b

--   
--   convert a list to a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a>   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="BitSet.intersection" >intersection</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a> α</b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a> α</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a> α</span> 
--   
--   <span class="code" >a `intersection` b</span> -- a set with all elements that are members of a and members of b   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="BitSet.intersectionE" >intersectionE</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Enum" >Enum</a> α ⇒ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a> α</b> → <b >α</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a> α</span>

--   
--   Predicate to tell if an element is a member of a set

--   
--   A set with one argument   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="BitSet.size" >size</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a> α</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></span>

--   <span class="code" >a `union` b</span> -- a set with all elements that are members of a or members of b

--   <span class="code" ><a name="BitSet.universal" >universal</a> ∷ (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Enum" >Enum</a> α, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bounded" >Bounded</a> α) ⇒ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet" >BitSet</a> α</span> 
--   
--   The universal set
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet
data BitSet e

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#BitSet.BitSet
BitSet {set ∷ Long}

-- | The <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> class defines bitwise operations over integral types. 
--   Bits are numbered from 0 with bit 0 being the least significant bit. 
--   Minimal complete definition: <span class="unknown" >.&.</span>, <span class="unknown" >.|.</span>, <span class="unknown" >.^.</span>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.complement" >Bits.complement</a>, (<a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a> or (<a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftL" >Bits.shiftL</a> and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftR" >Bits.shiftR</a>)), (<a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a> or (<a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateL" >Bits.rotateL</a> and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateR" >Bits.rotateR</a>)), <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.bitSize" >Bits.bitSize</a> and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.isSigned" >Bits.isSigned</a>. <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits_Long" >Long</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits_Int" >Int</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits_Integer" >Integer</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits._dot_amp_dot" >.&.</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → a → a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  11</span> 
--   
--   Bitwise \"and\"   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits._dot_caret_dot" >.^.</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → a → a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  10</span>

--   Bitwise \"xor\"

--  <b >infixl</b>  10</span> 
--   
--   Bitwise \"or\"   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.bit" >bit</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></b> → a</span> 
--   
--   <span class="code" >bit i</span> is a value with the <span class="code" >i</span>th bit set   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.bitCount" >bitCount</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></span> 
--   
--   Returns the number of one-bits in the two's complement binary representation of the specified value. 
--   Also known as "population count" or "Hamming Weight" of a bit string. 
--   See also <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamming_weight" >Hamming Weight</a>.  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.bitSize" >bitSize</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></span> 
--   
--   Return the number of bits in the type of the argument. The actual value of the argument is ignored. The function <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.bitSize" >Bits.bitSize</a> is undefined for types that do not have a fixed bitsize, like <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Integer" >Integer</a>.  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.clearBit" >clearBit</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a> → a</span> 
--   
--   <span class="code" >x \`clearBit\` i</span> is the same as <span class="code" >x .&. complement (bit i)</span>   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.complement" >complement</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → a</span> 
--   
--   Reverse all the bits in the argument   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.complementBit" >complementBit</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a> → a</span> 
--   
--   <span class="code" >x \`complementBit\` i</span> is the same as <span class="code" >x \`.^.\` bit i</span>   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.isSigned" >isSigned</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a></span> 
--   
--   Return <span class="unknown" >true</span> if the argument is a signed type. The actual value of the argument is ignored   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.rotate" >rotate</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ <b >a</b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></b> → a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  12</span> 
--   
--   <span class="code" ><a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a> x i</span> rotates <span class="code" >x</span> left by <span class="code" >i</span> bits if <span class="code" >i</span> is positive, or right by <span class="code" >-i</span> bits otherwise. 
--   For unbounded types like <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Integer" >Integer</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a> is equivalent to <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a>. 
--   An instance can define either this unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateL" >Bits.rotateL</a> and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateR" >Bits.rotateR</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.rotateL" >rotateL</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ <b >a</b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></b> → a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  12</span> 
--   
--   Rotate the argument left by the specified number of bits (which must be non-negative). 
--   An instance can define either this and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateR" >Bits.rotateR</a> or the unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.rotateR" >rotateR</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ <b >a</b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></b> → a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  12</span> 
--   
--   Rotate the argument right by the specified number of bits (which must be non-negative). 
--   An instance can define either this and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateL" >Bits.rotateL</a> or the unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.setBit" >setBit</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a> → a</span> 
--   
--   <span class="code" >x \`setBit\` i</span> is the same as <span class="code" >x .|. bit i</span>   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.shift" >shift</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ <b >a</b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></b> → a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  12</span> 
--   
--   <span class="code" ><a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a> x i</span> shifts <span class="code" >x</span> left by <span class="code" >i</span> bits if <span class="code" >i</span> is positive, or right by <span class="code" >-i</span> bits otherwise. Right shifts perform sign extension on signed number types; i.e. they fill the top bits with 1 if the <span class="code" >x</span> is negative and with 0 otherwise. 
--   An instance can define either this unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftL" >Bits.shiftL</a> and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftR" >Bits.shiftR</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.shiftL" >shiftL</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ <b >a</b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></b> → a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  12</span> 
--   
--   Shift the argument left by the specified number of bits (which must be non-negative). 
--   An instance can define either this and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftR" >Bits.shiftR</a> or the unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.shiftR" >shiftR</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ <b >a</b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></b> → a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  12</span> 
--   
--   Shift the first argument right by the specified number of bits (which must be non-negative). Right shifts perform sign extension on signed number types; i.e. they fill the top bits with 1 if the <span class="code" >x</span> is negative and with 0 otherwise. 
--   An instance can define either this and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftL" >Bits.shiftL</a> or the unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.testBit" >testBit</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a></span> 
--   
--   Return <span class="unknown" >true</span> if the <span class="code" >n</span>th bit of the argument is 1   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.ushiftR" >ushiftR</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a> → a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  12</span> 
--   
--   Unsigned shift right   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Bits.xor" >xor</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits" >Bits</a> a ⇒ a → a → a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  10</span>

--   Haskell compatibility. Same as `.^.`
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits
class (Eq a, Ord a, Num a) ⇒ Bits a

-- | Bitwise \"and\"
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits._dot_amp_dot
(.&.) ∷  Bits a ⇒ a → a → a 
infixl  11

-- | Bitwise \"xor\"
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits._dot_caret_dot
(.^.) ∷  Bits a ⇒ a → a → a 
infixl  10

-- | Bitwise \"or\"
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits._dot_bar_dot
(.|.) ∷  Bits a ⇒ a → a → a 
infixl  10

-- | <span class="code" >bit i</span> is a value with the <span class="code" >i</span>th bit set
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.bit
bit ∷ Bits a ⇒ Int → a

-- | Returns the number of one-bits in the two's complement binary representation of the specified value. 
--   Also known as "population count" or "Hamming Weight" of a bit string. 
--   See also <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamming_weight" >Hamming Weight</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.bitCount
bitCount ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int

-- | Return the number of bits in the type of the argument. The actual value of the argument is ignored. The function <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.bitSize" >Bits.bitSize</a> is undefined for types that do not have a fixed bitsize, like <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Integer" >Integer</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.bitSize
bitSize ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int

-- | <span class="code" >x \`clearBit\` i</span> is the same as <span class="code" >x .&. complement (bit i)</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.clearBit
clearBit ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → a

-- | Reverse all the bits in the argument
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.complement
complement ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → a

-- | <span class="code" >x \`complementBit\` i</span> is the same as <span class="code" >x \`.^.\` bit i</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.complementBit
complementBit ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → a

-- | Return <span class="unknown" >true</span> if the argument is a signed type. The actual value of the argument is ignored
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.isSigned
isSigned ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Bool

-- | <span class="code" ><a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a> x i</span> rotates <span class="code" >x</span> left by <span class="code" >i</span> bits if <span class="code" >i</span> is positive, or right by <span class="code" >-i</span> bits otherwise. 
--   For unbounded types like <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Integer" >Integer</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a> is equivalent to <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a>. 
--   An instance can define either this unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateL" >Bits.rotateL</a> and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateR" >Bits.rotateR</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate
rotate ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → a 
infixl  12

-- | Rotate the argument left by the specified number of bits (which must be non-negative). 
--   An instance can define either this and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateR" >Bits.rotateR</a> or the unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateL
rotateL ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → a 
infixl  12

-- | Rotate the argument right by the specified number of bits (which must be non-negative). 
--   An instance can define either this and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateL" >Bits.rotateL</a> or the unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotate" >Bits.rotate</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.rotateR
rotateR ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → a 
infixl  12

-- | <span class="code" >x \`setBit\` i</span> is the same as <span class="code" >x .|. bit i</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.setBit
setBit ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → a

-- | <span class="code" ><a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a> x i</span> shifts <span class="code" >x</span> left by <span class="code" >i</span> bits if <span class="code" >i</span> is positive, or right by <span class="code" >-i</span> bits otherwise. Right shifts perform sign extension on signed number types; i.e. they fill the top bits with 1 if the <span class="code" >x</span> is negative and with 0 otherwise. 
--   An instance can define either this unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftL" >Bits.shiftL</a> and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftR" >Bits.shiftR</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift
shift ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → a 
infixl  12

-- | Shift the argument left by the specified number of bits (which must be non-negative). 
--   An instance can define either this and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftR" >Bits.shiftR</a> or the unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftL
shiftL ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → a 
infixl  12

-- | Shift the first argument right by the specified number of bits (which must be non-negative). Right shifts perform sign extension on signed number types; i.e. they fill the top bits with 1 if the <span class="code" >x</span> is negative and with 0 otherwise. 
--   An instance can define either this and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftL" >Bits.shiftL</a> or the unified <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shift" >Bits.shift</a>, depending on which is more convenient for the type in question.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.shiftR
shiftR ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → a 
infixl  12

-- | Return <span class="unknown" >true</span> if the <span class="code" >n</span>th bit of the argument is 1
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.testBit
testBit ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → Bool

-- | Unsigned shift right
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.ushiftR
ushiftR ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → Int → a 
infixl  12

-- | Haskell compatibility. Same as `.^.`
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Bits#Bits.xor
xor ∷ Bits a ⇒ a → a → a 
infixl  10

-- | Haskell compatibility
module frege.data.Char

-- | The general categories for unicode characters and code points.  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="GeneralCategory.CATEGORY17" >CATEGORY17</a> </span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="GeneralCategory.COMBINING_SPACING_MARK" >COMBINING_SPACING_MARK</a> </span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="GeneralCategory.CONNECTOR_PUNCTUATION" >CONNECTOR_PUNCTUATION</a> </span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="GeneralCategory.CONTROL" >CONTROL</a> </span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="GeneralCategory.CURRENCY_SYMBOL" >CURRENCY_SYMBOL</a> </span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="GeneralCategory.DASH_PUNCTUATION" >DASH_PUNCTUATION</a> </span> 
--

-- | return the general category of a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Char" >Char</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#generalCategory
generalCategory ∷ Char → GeneralCategory

-- | Check if the argument is a control character.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isControl
isControl ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the argument is in the range '0'..'7'
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isOctDigit
isOctDigit ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the argument is a digit, in the range 'a'..'f' or in the range 'A'..'F'
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isHexDigit
isHexDigit ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#generalCategory" >generalCategory</a> of the argument is one of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.NON_SPACING_MARK" >GeneralCategory.NON_SPACING_MARK</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.ENCLOSING_MARK" >GeneralCategory.ENCLOSING_MARK</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.COMBINING_SPACING_MARK" >GeneralCategory.COMBINING_SPACING_MARK</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isMark
isMark ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#generalCategory" >generalCategory</a> of the argument is one of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.DECIMAL_DIGIT_NUMBER" >GeneralCategory.DECIMAL_DIGIT_NUMBER</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.LETTER_NUMBER" >GeneralCategory.LETTER_NUMBER</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.OTHER_NUMBER" >GeneralCategory.OTHER_NUMBER</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isNumber
isNumber ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#generalCategory" >generalCategory</a> of the argument is one of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.DASH_PUNCTUATION" >GeneralCategory.DASH_PUNCTUATION</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.START_PUNCTUATION" >GeneralCategory.START_PUNCTUATION</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.END_PUNCTUATION" >GeneralCategory.END_PUNCTUATION</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.CONNECTOR_PUNCTUATION" >GeneralCategory.CONNECTOR_PUNCTUATION</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.OTHER_PUNCTUATION" >GeneralCategory.OTHER_PUNCTUATION</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isPunctuation
isPunctuation ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#generalCategory" >generalCategory</a> of the argument is one of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.MATH_SYMBOL" >GeneralCategory.MATH_SYMBOL</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.CURRENCY_SYMBOL" >GeneralCategory.CURRENCY_SYMBOL</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.MODIFIER_SYMBOL" >GeneralCategory.MODIFIER_SYMBOL</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.OTHER_SYMBOL" >GeneralCategory.OTHER_SYMBOL</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isSymbol
isSymbol ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#generalCategory" >generalCategory</a> of the argument is one of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.SPACE_SEPARATOR" >GeneralCategory.SPACE_SEPARATOR</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.LINE_SEPARATOR" >GeneralCategory.LINE_SEPARATOR</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#GeneralCategory.PARAGRAPH_SEPARATOR" >GeneralCategory.PARAGRAPH_SEPARATOR</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isSeparator
isSeparator ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if a character is printable. 
--   True for a defined character that is neither a surrogate character nor a control character.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isPrint
isPrint ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the argument is from the ASCII character set.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isAscii
isAscii ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the argument is from the Latin1 character set.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isLatin1
isLatin1 ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the argument is an ASCII upper case letter.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isAsciiUpper
isAsciiUpper ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Check if the argument is an ASCII lower case letter.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#isAsciiLower
isAsciiLower ∷ Char → Bool

-- | Convert a hexadecimal digit to its <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a> value. 
--   For different number bases, see <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Char.digit" >Char.digit</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#digitToInt
digitToInt ∷ Char → Int

-- | Convert an <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a> in the range 0..15 to the corresponding hexadecimal digit. 
--   For other number bases than 16, see <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Char.forDigit" >Char.forDigit</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Char#intToDigit
intToDigit ∷ Int → Char

-- | Composition of two applicative functors <i >f</i> and <i >g</i> such that the type <i >f (g a)</i> can itself be treated as aplicative functor.
module frege.data.Compose

-- | <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Compose.Compose" >Compose</a> {run ∷ f (g a)}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Compose.run" >run</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Compose#Compose" >Compose</a> β α γ</b> → β (α γ)</span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >run</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Compose#Compose
data Compose f g a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Compose#Compose.Compose
Compose {run ∷ f (g a)}

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Compose#compose
compose ∷ f (g a) → Compose f g a

-- | co-product
module frege.data.Coproduct

-- | <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Coproduct.Inl" >Inl</a> (f a)</span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Coproduct.Inr" >Inr</a> (g a)</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Coproduct#Coproduct
data Coproduct f g a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Coproduct#Coproduct.Inl
Inl (f a)

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Coproduct#Coproduct.Inr
Inr (g a)

-- | Data structures that can be folded.
module frege.data.Foldable

-- | Data structures that can be folded. 
--   Minimal complete definition: <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable.foldMap" >Foldable.foldMap</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable.foldr" >Foldable.foldr</a>. 
--   For example, given a data type 
--  <pre>
--  
--   data Tree a = Empty | Leaf a | Node (Tree a) a (Tree a)
--  </pre> 
--   a suitable instance would be 
--  <pre>
--  
--   instance Foldable Tree where
--      foldMap f Empty = mempty
--      foldMap f (Leaf x) = f x
--      foldMap f (Node l k r) = foldMap f l `mappend` f k `mappend` foldMap f r
--  </pre> 
--   This is suitable even for abstract types, as the monoid is assumed to satisfy the monoid laws. Alternatively, one could define <span class="code" >foldr</span>: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   instance Foldable Tree where
--      foldr f z Empty = z
--      foldr f z (Leaf x) = f x z
--      foldr f z (Node l k r) = foldr f (f k (foldr f z r)) l
--  </pre> <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable_Maybe" >Maybe</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable_Identity" >Identity.Identity</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable__lbrack_rbrack" >[]</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Foldable.fold" >fold</a> ∷ (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable" >Foldable</a> t, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/./Monoid.html#Monoid" >Monoid</a> m) ⇒ <b >t m</b> → m</span> 
--   
--   Combine the elements of a structure using a monoid.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Foldable.fold1" >fold1</a> ∷ (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable" >Foldable</a> t, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/./Monoid.html#Semigroup" >Semigroup</a> m) ⇒ t m → m</span> 
--   
--   versions without base case 
--   A variant of fold that has no base case, and thus may only be applied to non-empty structures. 
--   (not in Haskell's Foldable, because they have no Semigroup)   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Foldable.foldMap" >foldMap</a> ∷ (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable" >Foldable</a> t, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/./Monoid.html#Monoid" >Monoid</a> m) ⇒ (a → m) → <b >t a</b> → m</span> 
--   
--   Map each element of the structure to a monoid, and combine the results.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Foldable.foldMap1" >foldMap1</a> ∷ (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable" >Foldable</a> t, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/./Monoid.html#Semigroup" >Semigroup</a> m) ⇒ (a → m) → t a → m</span> 
--   
--   A variant of foldMap that has no base case, and thus may only be applied to non-empty structures. 
--   (not in Haskell's Foldable, because they have no Semigroup)   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Foldable.foldl" >foldl</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable" >Foldable</a> t ⇒ (a → b → a) → a → <b >t b</b> → a</span> 
--   
--   Left-associative fold of a structure.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Foldable.foldl1" >foldl1</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable" >Foldable</a> t ⇒ (a → a → a) → <b >t a</b> → a</span> 
--   
--   nowarn: not easy enough 
--   A variant of foldl that has no base case, and thus may only be applied to non-empty structures.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Foldable.foldr" >foldr</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable" >Foldable</a> t ⇒ (a → b → b) → b → <b >t a</b> → b</span> 
--   
--   Right-associative fold of a structure.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Foldable.foldr1" >foldr1</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable" >Foldable</a> t ⇒ (a → a → a) → <b >t a</b> → a</span> 
--   
--   nowarn: not easy enough 
--   A variant of foldr that has no base case, and thus may only be applied to non-empty structures.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable
class Functor t ⇒ Foldable t

-- | Combine the elements of a structure using a monoid.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable.fold
fold ∷ (Foldable t, Monoid m) ⇒ t m → m

-- | versions without base case 
--   A variant of fold that has no base case, and thus may only be applied to non-empty structures. 
--   (not in Haskell's Foldable, because they have no Semigroup)
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable.fold1
fold1 ∷ (Foldable t, Semigroup m) ⇒ t m → m

-- | Map each element of the structure to a monoid, and combine the results.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable.foldMap
foldMap ∷ (Foldable t, Monoid m) ⇒ (a → m) → t a → m

-- | A variant of foldMap that has no base case, and thus may only be applied to non-empty structures. 
--   (not in Haskell's Foldable, because they have no Semigroup)
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable.foldMap1
foldMap1 ∷ (Foldable t, Semigroup m) ⇒ (a → m) → t a → m

-- | Left-associative fold of a structure.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable.foldl
foldl ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → b → a) → a → t b → a

-- | nowarn: not easy enough 
--   A variant of foldl that has no base case, and thus may only be applied to non-empty structures.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable.foldl1
foldl1 ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → a → a) → t a → a

-- | Right-associative fold of a structure.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable.foldr
foldr ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → b → b) → b → t a → b

-- | nowarn: not easy enough 
--   A variant of foldr that has no base case, and thus may only be applied to non-empty structures.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#Foldable.foldr1
foldr1 ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → a → a) → t a → a

-- | nowarn: not easy enough 
--   A variant of foldr that has no base case, and thus may only be applied to non-empty structures.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#foldr1α
foldr1α ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → a → a) → t a → a

-- | nowarn: not easy enough 
--   A variant of foldl that has no base case, and thus may only be applied to non-empty structures.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#foldl1α
foldl1α ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → a → a) → t a → a

-- | Fold over the elements of a structure, associating to the right, but strictly.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#foldr_tick
foldr' ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → b → b) → b → t a → b

-- | Monadic fold over the elements of a structure, associating to the right, i.e. from right to left.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#foldrM
foldrM ∷ (Foldable t, Monad m) ⇒ (a → b → m b) → b → t a → m b

-- | Fold over the elements of a structure, associating to the left, but strictly.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#foldl_tick
foldl' ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → b → a) → a → t b → a

-- | Monadic fold over the elements of a structure, associating to the left, i.e. from left to right.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#foldlM
foldlM ∷ (Foldable t, Monad m) ⇒ (a → b → m a) → a → t b → m a

-- | Map each element of a structure to an action, evaluate these actions from left to right, and ignore the results.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#traverse_
traverse_ ∷ (Foldable t, Applicative f) ⇒ (a → f b) → t a → f ()

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#for_" >for_</a> is <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#traverse_" >traverse_</a> with its arguments flipped.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#for_
for_ ∷ (Foldable t, Applicative f) ⇒ t a → (a → f b) → f ()

-- | Map each element of a structure to a monadic action, evaluate these actions from left to right, and ignore the results.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#mapM_
mapM_ ∷ (Foldable t, Monad m) ⇒ (a → m b) → t a → m ()

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#forM_" >forM_</a> is <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#mapM_" >mapM_</a> with its arguments flipped.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#forM_
forM_ ∷ (Foldable t, Monad m) ⇒ t a → (a → m b) → m ()

-- | Evaluate each action in the structure from left to right, and ignore the results.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#sequenceA_
sequenceA_ ∷ (Foldable t, Applicative f) ⇒ t (f a) → f ()

-- | Evaluate each monadic action in the structure from left to right, and ignore the results.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#sequence_
sequence_ ∷ (Foldable t, Monad m) ⇒ t (m a) → m ()

-- | The sum of a collection of actions, generalizing <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#concat" >concat</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#msum
msum ∷ (Foldable t, MonadPlus m) ⇒ t (m a) → m a

-- | The concatenation of all the elements of a container of lists.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#concat
concat ∷ Foldable t ⇒ t [a] → [a]

-- | Map a function over all the elements of a container and concatenate the resulting lists.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#concatMap
concatMap ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → [b]) → t a → [b]

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#and" >and</a> returns the conjunction of a container of Bools. For the result to be <b >true</b>, the container must be finite; <b >false</b>, however, results from a <b >false</b> value finitely far from the left end.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#and
and ∷ Foldable t ⇒ t Bool → Bool

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#or" >or</a> returns the disjunction of a container of Bools. For the result to be <b >false</b>, the container must be finite; <b >true</b>, however, results from a <b >true</b> value finitely far from the left end.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#or
or ∷ Foldable t ⇒ t Bool → Bool

-- | Determines whether any element of the structure satisfies the predicate.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#any
any ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → Bool) → t a → Bool

-- | Determines whether all elements of the structure satisfy the predicate.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#all
all ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → Bool) → t a → Bool

-- | The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#sum" >sum</a> function computes the sum of the numbers of a structure.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#sum
sum ∷ (Foldable t, Num a) ⇒ t a → a

-- | The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#product" >product</a> function computes the product of the numbers of a structure.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#product
product ∷ (Foldable t, Num a) ⇒ t a → a

-- | The largest element of a non-empty structure.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#maximum
maximum ∷ (Foldable t, Ord a) ⇒ t a → a

-- | The largest element of a non-empty structure with respect to the given comparison function.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#maximumBy
maximumBy ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → a → Ordering) → t a → a

-- | The least element of a non-empty structure.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#minimum
minimum ∷ (Foldable t, Ord a) ⇒ t a → a

-- | The least element of a non-empty structure with respect to the given comparison function.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#minimumBy
minimumBy ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → a → Ordering) → t a → a

-- | Does the element occur in the structure?
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#elem
elem ∷ (Foldable t, Eq a) ⇒ a → t a → Bool

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#notElem" >notElem</a> is the negation of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#elem" >elem</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#notElem
notElem ∷ (Foldable t, Eq a) ⇒ a → t a → Bool

-- | The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#find" >find</a> function takes a predicate and a structure and returns the leftmost element of the structure matching the predicate, or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Maybe.Nothing" >Maybe.Nothing</a> if there is no such element.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Foldable#find
find ∷ Foldable t ⇒ (a → Bool) → t a → Maybe a

-- | Module 
--   <div > Data.Graph </div>  
--   Copyright 
--   <div > (c) The University of Glasgow 2002 </div>  
--   License 
--   <div > BSD-style (see the file libraries/base/LICENSE) </div>  
--   A version of the graph algorithms described in:
--   <i >Lazy Depth-First Search and Linear Graph Algorithms in Haskell</i>, by David King and John Launchbury.
--   Ported to Frege from the Haskell library source.
module frege.data.Graph

-- | Strongly connected component.  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="SCC.AcyclicSCC" >AcyclicSCC</a> vertex</span> 
--   
--   A single vertex that is not in any cycle.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="SCC.CyclicSCC" >CyclicSCC</a> [vertex]</span> 
--   
--   A maximal set of mutually reachable vertices.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#SCC
data SCC vertex

-- | A single vertex that is not in any cycle.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#SCC.AcyclicSCC
AcyclicSCC vertex

-- | A maximal set of mutually reachable vertices.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#SCC.CyclicSCC
CyclicSCC [vertex]

-- | The vertices of a list of strongly connected components.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#flattenSCCs
flattenSCCs ∷ [SCC a] → [a]

-- | The vertices of a strongly connected component.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#flattenSCC
flattenSCC ∷ SCC vertex → [vertex]

-- | Make a (key, [key]) list into one that is accepted by <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#stronglyConnComp" >stronglyConnComp</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#edgeFromTuple
edgeFromTuple ∷ (α, β) → (α, α, β)

-- | Convenience function to compute topologically sorted strongly connected components of an adjacency list of the form: 
--  <pre>
--  
--    [(key, [key])]
--  </pre> 
--   The result will be a list of lists of <i >keys</i>, where a singleton indicates no mutual dependency with other keys and a list consisting of several keys means that those are mutually dependend on each other. 
--   In addition, earlier elements will not depend on later ones. 
--   If the result contains only singletons, then the input was an acyclic graph.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#stronglyConnectedComponents
stronglyConnectedComponents ∷ Ord key ⇒ [(key, [key])] → [[key]]

-- | The strongly connected components of a directed graph, topologically sorted. 
--   The graph is a list of nodes uniquely identified by keys, with a list of keys of nodes this node has edges to. The latter one may contain keys that don't correspond to nodes of the graph; such edges are ignored.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#stronglyConnComp
stronglyConnComp ∷ Ord key ⇒ [(node, key, [key])] → [SCC node]

-- | The strongly connected components of a directed graph, topologically sorted. The function is the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#stronglyConnComp" >stronglyConnComp</a>, except that all the information about each node retained. 
--   This interface is used when you expect to apply <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#SCC" >SCC</a> to (some of) the result of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/data/Graph#SCC" >SCC</a>, so you don't want to lose the dependency information.
