-- | <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a> values are based on Java's primitive <span class="code" >long</span> values. 
--   According to the Java Language Specification, <span class="code" >long</span> values are 64 bit wide signed two's complement integers (§4.2). Java operations on <span class="code" >long</span> do not indicate overflow or underflow in any way (§4.2.2). Instead, just the low 64 bits of every result are retained. <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Long._dot_amp_dot" >.&.</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a></b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>&<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  11</span> 
--   
--   Computes binary <i >and</i> of two integers. Uses the java <span class="code" >&</span>-operator.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Long._dot_caret_dot" >.^.</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a></b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>^<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  10</span>

-- | Convert an <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a> to a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double" >Double</a>, i.e. <span class="code" >42L.double == 42.0</span>.

-- | <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a> values are based on Java's primitive <span class="code" >char</span> values. 
--   This type has many native functions based on the methods in <span class="code" >java.lang.Character</span>. 
--   Most <span class="code" >is...</span> functions work on <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a> and <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a> (codepoint). 
--   Likewise, most <span class="code" >to...Case</span> functions work on codepoints.  <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.digit" >digit</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a></b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Character.digit</span> 
--   
--   Returns the numeric value of the character argument in the specified radix. 
--   If the character is not a digit in the given radix, -1 is returned. 
--   The radix must be in the range 2..36, otherwise also -1 is returned.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.forDigit" >forDigit</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a></b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Character.forDigit</span> 
--   
--  <pre>
--  
--   Char.forDigit d r
--  </pre> 
--   returns the character for the digit <i >d</i> in radix <i >r</i> 
--   <i >d</i> must not be negative and lower than <i >r</i>, and <i >r</i> must be in the range 2..36 
--   When the arguments are invalid the character '\u0000' is returned.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.getName" >getName</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Maybe" >Maybe</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a><br ></br>

--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.highSurrogate" >highSurrogate</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Character.highSurrogate</span> 
--   
--   The leading surrogate (which is a high surrogate code unit) of the surrogate pair representing the specified supplementary character (Unicode code point) in the UTF-16 encoding. 
--   If the specified value is not a supplementary character, an unspecified character is returned. 
--   See also: <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint" >Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.lowSurrogate" >Char.lowSurrogate</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.toCodePoint" >Char.toCodePoint</a> 
--   The following holds: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   isSupplementaryCodePoint x ==&gt; (x == toCodePoint (highSurrogate x) (lowSurrogate x))
--  </pre>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.isDefined" >isDefined</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bool" >Bool</a><br ></br>

--   Determines if a character (Unicode code point) is defined in Unicode. 
--   A character is defined if at least one of the following is true: <ul > <li > It has an entry in the UnicodeData file. </li> <li > It has a value in a range defined by the UnicodeData file. </li> </ul>

--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint" >isSupplementaryCodePoint</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bool" >Bool</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Character.isSupplementaryCodePoint</span> 
--   
--   Determines whether the specified character (Unicode code point) is in the supplementary character range. 
--   This is roughly equivalent to 
--  <pre>
--  
--   (&gt; ord Char.maxBound)
--  </pre> 
--   except that it also checks if the value is lower than <span class="code" >0x110000</span> 
--   If, for some integer <span class="code" >n</span> 
--  <pre>
--  
--   not (Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint n) &amp;&amp; (n &gt; ord Char.maxBound)
--  </pre> 
--   then <span class="code" >n</span> is not a codepoint at all.  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.isSurrogate" >isSurrogate</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bool" >Bool</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Character.isSurrogate</span> 
--   
--   Determines if the given char value is a Unicode surrogate code unit. 
--   Such values do not represent characters by themselves, but are used in the representation of supplementary characters in the UTF-16 encoding. 
--   A char value is a surrogate code unit if and only if it is either a low-surrogate code unit or a high-surrogate code unit.  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.isSurrogatePair" >isSurrogatePair</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a></b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bool" >Bool</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Character.isSurrogatePair</span> 
--   
--   Determines whether the specified pair of char values is a valid Unicode surrogate pair.

--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.lowSurrogate" >lowSurrogate</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Character.lowSurrogate</span> 
--   
--   The trailing surrogate (which is a low surrogate code unit) of the surrogate pair representing the specified supplementary character (Unicode code point) in the UTF-16 encoding. 
--   If the specified value is not a supplementary character, an unspecified character is returned. 
--   See also: <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint" >Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.highSurrogate" >Char.highSurrogate</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.toCodePoint" >Char.toCodePoint</a> 
--   The following holds: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   isSupplementaryCodePoint x ==&gt; (x == toCodePoint (highSurrogate x) (lowSurrogate x))
--  </pre>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.toCodePoint" >toCodePoint</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a></b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Character.toCodePoint</span> 
--   
--  <pre>
--  
--   Char.toCodePoint high low
--  </pre> 
--   Converts the specified surrogate pair to its supplementary code point value. This function does not validate the specified surrogate pair. The caller must validate it using <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.isSurrogatePair" >Char.isSurrogatePair</a> if necessary.  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.toLowerCase" >toLowerCase</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a><br ></br>
--               | <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Character.toLowerCase</span> 
--   
--   The lowercase equivalent of the character, if any; otherwise, the character itself.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Char.toLowerCaseα" >toLowerCaseα</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Character.toLowerCase  <b >overloads </b><a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.toLowerCase" >toLowerCase</a></span>

-- | Returns the numeric value of the character argument in the specified radix. 
--   If the character is not a digit in the given radix, -1 is returned. 
--   The radix must be in the range 2..36, otherwise also -1 is returned.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.digit
digit ∷ Char → Int → Int 
pure native java.lang.Character.digit

-- | <pre>
--  
--   Char.forDigit d r
--  </pre> 
--   returns the character for the digit <i >d</i> in radix <i >r</i> 
--   <i >d</i> must not be negative and lower than <i >r</i>, and <i >r</i> must be in the range 2..36 
--   When the arguments are invalid the character '\u0000' is returned.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.forDigit
forDigit ∷ Int → Int → Char 
pure native java.lang.Character.forDigit

-- | The leading surrogate (which is a high surrogate code unit) of the surrogate pair representing the specified supplementary character (Unicode code point) in the UTF-16 encoding. 
--   If the specified value is not a supplementary character, an unspecified character is returned. 
--   See also: <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint" >Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.lowSurrogate" >Char.lowSurrogate</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.toCodePoint" >Char.toCodePoint</a> 
--   The following holds: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   isSupplementaryCodePoint x ==&gt; (x == toCodePoint (highSurrogate x) (lowSurrogate x))
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.highSurrogate
highSurrogate ∷ Int → Char 
pure native java.lang.Character.highSurrogate

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.isDefined

           | Int → Bool 
pure native java.lang.Character.isDefined

-- | Determines whether the specified character (Unicode code point) is in the supplementary character range. 
--   This is roughly equivalent to 
--  <pre>
--  
--   (&gt; ord Char.maxBound)
--  </pre> 
--   except that it also checks if the value is lower than <span class="code" >0x110000</span> 
--   If, for some integer <span class="code" >n</span> 
--  <pre>
--  
--   not (Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint n) &amp;&amp; (n &gt; ord Char.maxBound)
--  </pre> 
--   then <span class="code" >n</span> is not a codepoint at all.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint
isSupplementaryCodePoint ∷ Int → Bool 
pure native java.lang.Character.isSupplementaryCodePoint

-- | Determines if the given char value is a Unicode surrogate code unit. 
--   Such values do not represent characters by themselves, but are used in the representation of supplementary characters in the UTF-16 encoding. 
--   A char value is a surrogate code unit if and only if it is either a low-surrogate code unit or a high-surrogate code unit.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.isSurrogate
isSurrogate ∷ Char → Bool 
pure native java.lang.Character.isSurrogate

-- | The trailing surrogate (which is a low surrogate code unit) of the surrogate pair representing the specified supplementary character (Unicode code point) in the UTF-16 encoding. 
--   If the specified value is not a supplementary character, an unspecified character is returned. 
--   See also: <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint" >Char.isSupplementaryCodePoint</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.highSurrogate" >Char.highSurrogate</a>, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.toCodePoint" >Char.toCodePoint</a>

--  <pre>

--   isSupplementaryCodePoint x ==&gt; (x == toCodePoint (highSurrogate x) (lowSurrogate x))
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.lowSurrogate
lowSurrogate ∷ Int → Char 
pure native java.lang.Character.lowSurrogate

-- | <pre>
--  
--   Char.toCodePoint high low
--  </pre> 
--   Converts the specified surrogate pair to its supplementary code point value. This function does not validate the specified surrogate pair. The caller must validate it using <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.isSurrogatePair" >Char.isSurrogatePair</a> if necessary.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char.toCodePoint

pure native java.lang.Character.toCodePoint

-- | <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a> values are based on Java's <span class="code" >java.lang.String</span> objects. <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a> is an alias for <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ" >StringJ</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Char" >Char</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String
type String = StringJ Char

-- | For technical reasons, the native string type is defined with a phantom type, which allows us to treat strings like character lists. 
--   The following rules apply: <ul > <li > There must be no polymorphic non empty string. Trying to extract elements from it with <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ.charAt" >StringJ.charAt</a> would fail with an exception at runtime.</li> <li > Every function with return type (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ" >StringJ</a> a) must either take one or more arguments of the same type which it manipulates, or it must return the empty string. In the former case, the elements of the result string must all be computed from the elements of the argument strings.</li> </ul> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StringJ._plus_plus" >++</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ" >StringJ</a> a</b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ" >StringJ</a> a</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ" >StringJ</a> a<br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>+<br ></br>
--  <b >infixr</b>  13</span> 
--   
--   Concatenate two strings, uses Java's <span class="code" >+</span> operator   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StringJ.atod" >atod</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double" >Double</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Double.parseDouble</span> 
--   
--   Like <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ._double" >StringJ.double</a>, but the exception is not checked, thus only good when one <b >knows for sure</b> that the parse will succeed.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StringJ.atof" >atof</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Float" >Float</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Float.parseFloat</span> 
--   
--   Like <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ._float" >StringJ.float</a>, but the exception is not checked, thus only good when one <b >knows for sure</b> that the parse will succeed.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StringJ.atoi" >atoi</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Integer.parseInt</span> 
--   
--   Like <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ._int" >StringJ.int</a>, but the exception is not checked, thus only good when one <b >knows for sure</b> that the parse will succeed.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StringJ.atol" >atol</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Long.parseLong</span> 
--   
--   Like <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ._long" >StringJ.long</a>, but the exception is not checked, thus only good when one <b >knows for sure</b> that the parse will succeed.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StringJ.aton" >aton</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Integer" >Integer</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>new</span> 
--   
--   Like <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ.integer" >StringJ.integer</a>, but the exception is not checked, thus only good when one <b >knows for sure</b> that the parse will succeed.

--   <span class="code" ><a name="StringJ._int" >int</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a></b> → (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#NumberFormatException" >NumberFormatException</a> | <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a>)<br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Integer.parseInt</span> 
--   
--   Safe way to parse an integer from a string. <span class="code" >java.lang.NumberFormatException</span> will be caught and returned as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Either.Left" >Either.Left</a> value. When the parse succeeds, the integer is returned in the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Either.Right" >Either.Right</a> value. 
--   Use like this: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   case s.int of
--     Left exc -&gt; ...     -- s is not well formed
--     Right i  -&gt; ...     -- the parsed value is in i
--  </pre>

--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>substring</span> 
--   
--   see <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#substr" >substr</a>

--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>toLowerCase</span> 
--   
--   convert to lower case   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StringJ.toUpperCase" >toUpperCase</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>toUpperCase</span> 
--   
--   convert to upper case   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="StringJ.wait" >wait</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#IO" >IO</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Unit" >()</a><br ></br>

-- | Safe way to parse an integer from a string. <span class="code" >java.lang.NumberFormatException</span> will be caught and returned as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Either.Left" >Either.Left</a> value. When the parse succeeds, the integer is returned in the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Either.Right" >Either.Right</a> value. 
--   Use like this: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   case s.int of
--     Left exc -&gt; ...     -- s is not well formed
--     Right i  -&gt; ...     -- the parsed value is in i
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#StringJ._int
int ∷ String → (NumberFormatException | Int) 
pure native java.lang.Integer.parseInt

-- | <span class="code" >substr s start end</span> returns the sub string of <span class="code" >s</span> that starts with the character at position <span class="code" >start</span> and extends to the character at position <span class="code" >end-1</span>. 
--   This uses the native method <span class="code" >substring</span> of class <span class="code" >java.lang.String</span>. It will throw an <span class="code" >IndexOutOfBoundsException</span> if <span class="code" >start</span> is negative or larger than <span class="code" >end</span> or if <span class="code" >end</span> is greater than the length of <span class="code" >s</span>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#substr

pure native substring

-- | <span class="code" >strtail s n</span> returns a new string that is a substring of string <i >s</i>. The substring begins with the character at the specified index and extends to the end of <i >s</i>. 
--   This uses the native method <span class="code" >substring</span> of class <span class="code" >java.lang.String</span>. It will throw an <span class="code" >IndexOutOfBoundsException</span> if <i >n</i> is negative or larger than the length of <i >s</i>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#strtail

-- | <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Float" >Float</a> values are based on Java's primitive <span class="code" >float</span> values. 
--   According to the Java Language Specification §4.2.3, <span class="code" >float</span> values are 32-bit-precision binary floating point values. The values and the operations on it behave as specified in the IEEE Standard for Binary Floating-Point Arithmetic. <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Float._double" >double</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Float" >Float</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double" >Double</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>(double)</span> 
--   
--   Applies the java widening primitive conversion from <span class="code" >float</span> to <span class="code" >double</span>.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Float._int" >int</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Float" >Float</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Math.round</span> 
--   
--   Returns the closest <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a> value to the argument. The result is rounded to an integer by adding 1/2, taking the <a href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./Math.html#floor" >floor</a> of the result, and casting the result to type int. 
--   The following property holds: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   (f &lt; Int.maxBound.float &amp;&amp; f &gt; Int.minBound.float) ==&gt;
--     (f.int.float == (f + 0.5f).floor)
--  </pre> 
--   Special cases: <ul > <li > If the argument is NaN, the result is 0. </li> <li > If the argument is negative infinity or any value less than or equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Int.minBound" >Bounded_Int.minBound</a>, the result is equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Int.minBound" >Bounded_Int.minBound</a>.</li> <li > If the argument is positive infinity or any value greater than or equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Int.maxBound" >Bounded_Int.maxBound</a>, the result is equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Int.maxBound" >Bounded_Int.maxBound</a>.</li> </ul>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Float
data Float 

-- | Applies the java widening primitive conversion from <span class="code" >float</span> to <span class="code" >double</span>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Float._double
double ∷ Float → Double 
pure native (double)

-- | Returns the closest <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Int" >Int</a> value to the argument. The result is rounded to an integer by adding 1/2, taking the <a href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./Math.html#floor" >floor</a> of the result, and casting the result to type int. 
--   The following property holds: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   (f &lt; Int.maxBound.float &amp;&amp; f &gt; Int.minBound.float) ==&gt;
--     (f.int.float == (f + 0.5f).floor)
--  </pre> 
--   Special cases: <ul > <li > If the argument is NaN, the result is 0. </li> <li > If the argument is negative infinity or any value less than or equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Int.minBound" >Bounded_Int.minBound</a>, the result is equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Int.minBound" >Bounded_Int.minBound</a>.</li> <li > If the argument is positive infinity or any value greater than or equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Int.maxBound" >Bounded_Int.maxBound</a>, the result is equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Int.maxBound" >Bounded_Int.maxBound</a>.</li> </ul>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Float._int
int ∷ Float → Int 
pure native java.lang.Math.round

-- | <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double" >Double</a> values are Java's primitive <span class="code" >double</span> values. 
--   According to the Java Language Specification §4.2.3, <span class="code" >double</span> values are 64-bit-precision binary floating point values. The values and the operations on it behave as specified in the IEEE Standard for Binary Floating-Point Arithmetic. <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Double._float" >float</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double" >Double</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Float" >Float</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>(float)</span> 
--   
--   Applies the java narrowing primitive conversion from <span class="code" >double</span> to <span class="code" >float</span>   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Double._long" >long</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double" >Double</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Math.round</span> 
--   
--   Returns the closest <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a> value to the argument. The result is rounded to an integer by adding 1/2, taking the <a href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./Math.html#floor" >floor</a> of the result, and casting the result to type <span class="code" >long</span>. 
--   The following property holds: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   (d &lt; Long.maxBound.double &amp;&amp; d &gt; Long.minBound.double) ==&gt;
--     (d.long.double == (d + 0.5d).floor)
--  </pre> 
--   Special cases: <ul > <li > If the argument is NaN, the result is 0. </li> <li > If the argument is negative infinity or any value less than or equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Long.minBound" >Bounded_Long.minBound</a>, the result is equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Long.minBound" >Bounded_Long.minBound</a>.</li> <li > If the argument is positive infinity or any value greater than or equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Long.maxBound" >Bounded_Long.maxBound</a>, the result is equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Long.maxBound" >Bounded_Long.maxBound</a>.</li> </ul>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Double.longBits" >longBits</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double" >Double</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>java.lang.Double.doubleToLongBits</span> 
--   
--   bit representation of a double
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double
data Double 

-- | Applies the java narrowing primitive conversion from <span class="code" >double</span> to <span class="code" >float</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double._float
float ∷ Double → Float 
pure native (float)

-- | Returns the closest <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Long" >Long</a> value to the argument. The result is rounded to an integer by adding 1/2, taking the <a href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./Math.html#floor" >floor</a> of the result, and casting the result to type <span class="code" >long</span>. 
--   The following property holds: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   (d &lt; Long.maxBound.double &amp;&amp; d &gt; Long.minBound.double) ==&gt;
--     (d.long.double == (d + 0.5d).floor)
--  </pre> 
--   Special cases: <ul > <li > If the argument is NaN, the result is 0. </li> <li > If the argument is negative infinity or any value less than or equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Long.minBound" >Bounded_Long.minBound</a>, the result is equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Long.minBound" >Bounded_Long.minBound</a>.</li> <li > If the argument is positive infinity or any value greater than or equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Long.maxBound" >Bounded_Long.maxBound</a>, the result is equal to the value of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bounded_Long.maxBound" >Bounded_Long.maxBound</a>.</li> </ul>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double._long
long ∷ Double → Long 
pure native java.lang.Math.round

-- | bit representation of a double
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Double.longBits
longBits ∷ Double → Long 
pure native java.lang.Double.doubleToLongBits

-- | The Java Object type <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Object.getClass" >getClass</a> ∷ <b >a</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Class" >Class</a> a<br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>frege.runtime.Runtime.getClass</span> 
--   
--   for any value, we can get its <span class="code" >Java</span> class   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Object.notify" >notify</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Object" >Object</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#IO" >IO</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Unit" >()</a><br ></br>
--  <b >native </b>frege.runtime.Concurrent.notifyOne</span> 
--   
--   notify a single thread waiting on the objects monitor   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Object.notifyAll" >notifyAll</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Object" >Object</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#IO" >IO</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Unit" >()</a><br ></br>
--  <b >native </b>frege.runtime.Concurrent.notifyAll</span> 
--   
--   notify all threads waiting on the objects monitor   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Object.wait" >wait</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Object" >Object</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#IO" >IO</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Unit" >()</a><br ></br>
--  <b >native </b>frege.runtime.Concurrent.waitFor  <b >throws </b><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#InterruptedException" >InterruptedException</a></span> 
--   
--   wait on <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Object" >Object</a>s monitor
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Object
data Object

data InterruptedException 

-- | warning: probably catches more exceptions than you want to handle, use (Exception1|Exception2|Result) This is the principal return type for java methods that are expected to throw exceptions. 
--   It is strongly recommended to use more specific exception types.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#CatchAll
type CatchAll = Either Throwable

-- | We need to do some reflection from frege code. For example, when we catch a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Throwable" >Throwable</a> thrown from Java code. we might want to know what it is. <h3 > Member Functions</h3>

--  <b >native </b>java.lang.Class.forName</span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Class.getName" >getName</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Class" >Class</a> a</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>getName</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Class
data Class a 

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Class.forName

native java.lang.Class.forName

-- | Constructs a strict tuple. 
--   The difference to <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Tuple2" >(,)</a> is that both argument values will be evaluated before the tuple is constructed. Thus: 
--  <pre>
--  
--  fst (42; undefined) == undefined
--  fst (42, undefined) == 42
--  </pre> 
--   <b >Implementation specific:</b> The compiler will rewrite <span class="code" >(a;b)</span> as <span class="code" >(PreludeBase.strictTuple2 a b)</span>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#strictTuple2
strictTuple2 ∷ a → b → (a, b) 
pure native PreludeBase.TTuple2.mk

-- | Constructs a strict 3-tuple. See remarks for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#strictTuple2" >strictTuple2</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#strictTuple3
strictTuple3 ∷ a → b → c → (a, b, c) 
pure native PreludeBase.TTuple3.mk

-- | Constructs a strict 4-tuple. See remarks for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#strictTuple2" >strictTuple2</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#strictTuple4

strictTuple24 ∷ a → b → c → d → e → f → g → h → i → j → k → l → m → n → o → p → q → r → s → t → u → v → w → x → (a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i, j, k, l, m, n, o, p, q, r, s, t, u, v, w, x) 
pure native PreludeBase.TTuple24.mk

strictTuple25 ∷ a → b → c → d → e → f → g → h → i → j → k → l → m → n → o → p → q → r → s → t → u → v → w → x → y → (a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i, j, k, l, m, n, o, p, q, r, s, t, u, v, w, x, y)

-- | <span class="code" >a `seq` b</span> evaluates <i >a</i> before it returns <i >b</i> 
--   This is a right associative operator with precedence 15.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#seq
seq ∷ α → β → β 
infixr  2

-- | An unchecked subclass of <span class="code" >java.lang.RuntimeException</span> for the Frege Runtime 
--   An instance of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a> will be thrown if <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#undefined" >undefined</a> or (<a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#error" >error</a> msg) is evaluated.  <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Undefined.die" >die</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Bool" >Bool</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>die</span> 
--   
--   Throw this <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a>, this will abort the computation evaluating it. 
--   Actually, the return type is not correct, since it never returns.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Undefined._new" >new</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a><br ></br>
--       | <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Throwable" >Throwable</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>new</span> 
--   
--   create an <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a> value with a message (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a>) or with a message and a cause. The cause is another exception that caused this one.

--   <span class="code" ><a name="Undefined.newα" >newα</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a><br ></br>
--  <b >pure </b><b >native </b>new  <b >overloads </b><a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined._new" >new</a></span> 
--   
--   create an <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a> value with a message (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a>) or with a message and a cause. The cause is another exception that caused this one.  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Undefined.newβ" >newβ</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a></b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Throwable" >Throwable</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a><br ></br>

--   create an <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a> value with a message (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#String" >String</a>) or with a message and a cause. @url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined
data Undefined 

-- | Throw this <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeBase#Undefined" >Undefined</a>, this will abort the computation evaluating it.
