(<+>) ∷  MonadAlt f ⇒ f a → f a → f a 
infixr  13

-- | The <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> class defines the basic operations over a <i >monad</i>, a concept from a branch of mathematics known as <i >category theory</i>. From the perspective of a Frege programmer, however, it is best to think of a monad as an <i >abstract datatype</i> of actions. 
--   Frege’s <b ><span class="code" >do</span></b> expressions provide a convenient syntax for writing monadic expressions. 
--   Instances of Monad should satisfy the following laws: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   return a &gt;&gt;= k == k a
--   m &gt;&gt;= return == m
--   m &gt;&gt;= (\x -&gt; k x &gt;&gt;= h) == (m &gt;&gt;= k) &gt;&gt;= h
--  </pre> 
--   Since instances of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> are also instances of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Functor" >Functor</a>, they additionally shall satisfy the law: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   fmap f xs == xs &gt;&gt;= return &bull; f
--  </pre> 
--   which is also the default implementation of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Functor.fmap" >Functor.fmap</a>. 
--   The instances of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> for lists, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#Maybe" >Maybe</a> and <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#ST" >ST</a> defined in the Prelude satisfy these laws. 
--   Minimal complete definition: <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Bind._gt_gt_eq" >Bind.>>=</a> and (<a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Applicative.pure" >Applicative.pure</a> or <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad._return" >Monad.return</a>) <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad_Either" >Either</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad__minus_gt" >-></a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad_ST" >ST</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad__lbrack_rbrack" >[]</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Monad._lt_star_gt" ><*></a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> m ⇒ m (a→b) → m a → m b<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  4</span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Monad._gt_gt" >>></a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> m ⇒ m a → m b → m b<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  3</span> 
--   
--   Sequentially compose two actions, discarding any value produced by the first, this works like sequencing operators (such as the semicolon) in imperative languages.  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Monad.fmap" >fmap</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> m ⇒ (a → b) → m a → m b<br ></br>
--  <b >infixl</b>  4</span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Monad.join" >join</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> m ⇒ m (m a) → m a</span> 
--   
--   The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad.join" >Monad.join</a> function is the conventional monad <b >join</b> operator. It is used to remove one level of monadic structure, projecting its bound argument into the outer level.  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Monad.pure" >pure</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> m ⇒ <b >a</b> → m a</span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Monad._return" >return</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> m ⇒ <b >a</b> → m a</span> 
--   
--   Inject a value into the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a>. This is the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Applicative.pure" >Applicative.pure</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad
class (Functor m, Apply m, Bind m, Applicative m) ⇒ Monad m

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad._lt_star_gt
(<*>) ∷  Monad m ⇒ m (a→b) → m a → m b 
infixl  4

-- | Sequentially compose two actions, discarding any value produced by the first, this works like sequencing operators (such as the semicolon) in imperative languages.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad._gt_gt
(>>) ∷  Monad m ⇒ m a → m b → m b 
infixl  3

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad.fmap
fmap ∷ Monad m ⇒ (a → b) → m a → m b 
infixl  4

-- | The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad.join" >Monad.join</a> function is the conventional monad <b >join</b> operator. It is used to remove one level of monadic structure, projecting its bound argument into the outer level.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad.join
join ∷ Monad m ⇒ m (m a) → m a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad.pure
pure ∷ Monad m ⇒ a → m a

-- | Inject a value into the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a>. This is the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Applicative.pure" >Applicative.pure</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad._return
return ∷ Monad m ⇒ a → m a

-- | The <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadFail" >MonadFail</a> class augments <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> by adding the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadFail.fail" >MonadFail.fail</a> operation. This operation is not part of the mathematical definition of a monad. <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadFail__lbrack_rbrack" >[]</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadFail_Either" >Either</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadFail_ST" >ST</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MonadFail.fail" >fail</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadFail" >MonadFail</a> m ⇒ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a></b> → m a</span> 
--   
--   Fail with a message.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadFail
class (Functor m, Apply m, Bind m, Applicative m, Monad m) ⇒ MonadFail m

-- | Fail with a message.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadFail.fail
fail ∷ MonadFail m ⇒ String → m a

-- | A <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> with a left identity. <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadPlus__lbrack_rbrack" >[]</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MonadZero.mzero" >mzero</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadZero" >MonadZero</a> mz ⇒ mz a</span> 
--   
--   This value should satisfy <i >left zero</i>: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   mzero &gt;&gt;= f = mzero   
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadZero
class (Functor mz, Apply mz, Bind mz, Applicative mz, Monad mz) ⇒ MonadZero mz

-- | This value should satisfy <i >left zero</i>: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   mzero &gt;&gt;= f = mzero   
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadZero.mzero
mzero ∷ MonadZero mz ⇒ mz a

-- | A <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad" >Monad</a> that also supports choice and failure and observes the following laws: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   mzero `mplus`  v = v
--   v `mplus` mzero  = v
--   (a `mplus` b) `mplus` c = a `mplus` (b `mplus` c)
--   (a `mplus` b) &gt;&gt;= f = (a &gt;&gt;= f) `mplus` (b &gt;&gt;= f)
--  </pre> <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadPlus__lbrack_rbrack" >[]</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MonadPlus.mplus" >mplus</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadPlus" >MonadPlus</a> mp ⇒ mp a → mp a → mp a<br ></br>
--  <b >infixr</b>  13</span> 
--   
--   an associative operation
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadPlus
class (Functor mp, Apply mp, Bind mp, Applicative mp, Monad mp, MonadZero mp) ⇒ MonadPlus mp

-- | an associative operation
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadPlus.mplus
mplus ∷ MonadPlus mp ⇒ mp a → mp a → mp a 
infixr  13

-- | <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="MonadOr.orElse" >orElse</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadOr" >MonadOr</a> mo ⇒ mo a → mo a → mo a</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadOr
class (Functor mo, Apply mo, Bind mo, Applicative mo, Monad mo, MonadZero mo) ⇒ MonadOr mo

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadOr.orElse
orElse ∷ MonadOr mo ⇒ mo a → mo a → mo a

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#_eq_lt_lt" >=<<</a> is the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Bind._gt_gt_eq" >Bind.>>=</a> with the arguments flipped
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#_eq_lt_lt
(=<<) ∷  Bind β ⇒ (α→β γ) → β α → β γ 
infixr  2

-- | left to right Kleisli composition of monads
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#_gt_eq_gt
(>=>) ∷  Bind δ ⇒ (α→δ β) → (β→δ γ) → α → δ γ 
infixr  3

-- | Right-to-left Kleisli composition of monads. (<a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#_gt_eq_gt" >>=></a>), with the arguments flipped
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#_lt_eq_lt
(<=<) ∷  Bind δ ⇒ (γ→δ β) → (α→δ γ) → α → δ β 
infixr  3

-- | nowarn: deep recursion possible 
--   repeat action forever
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#forever
forever ∷ Monad α ⇒ α γ → α β

-- | discard or ignore result of evaluation, such as the return value of an <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> action.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#_void
void ∷ Functor α ⇒ α β → α ()

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#msum" >msum</a> generalizes the list-based <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeList.html#concat" >concat</a> function.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#msum
msum ∷ MonadPlus α ⇒ [α β] → α β

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#filterM" >filterM</a> generalizes the list-based <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeList.html#filter" >filter</a> function.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#filterM
filterM ∷ Monad α ⇒ (β→α Bool) → [β] → α [β]

-- | Version of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#filterM" >filterM</a> that works on small lists with length < 1000 only. 
--   Beware of stack overflow, and use <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#filterM" >filterM</a>, when in doubt.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#shortFilterM
shortFilterM ∷ Monad α ⇒ (β→α Bool) → [β] → α [β]

-- | <span class="code" >replicateM n act</span> performs the action <span class="code" >n</span> times, gathering the results.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#replicateM
replicateM ∷ Monad m ⇒ Int → m a → m [a]

-- | Like <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#replicateM" >replicateM</a>, but discards the result.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#replicateM_
replicateM_ ∷ Monad m ⇒ Int → m a → m ()

-- | In many situations, the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#liftM" >liftM</a> operations can be replaced by uses of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#ap" >ap</a>, which promotes function application. 
--  <pre>
--  
--         return f `ap` x1 `ap` ... `ap` xn
--  </pre> 
--   is equivalent to 
--  <pre>
--  
--         liftMn f x1 x2 ... xn
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#ap
ap ∷ Monad α ⇒ α (γ→β) → α γ → α β

-- | Promote a function to a monad.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#liftM
liftM ∷ Monad m ⇒ (a → b) → m a → m b

-- | Promote a function to a monad, scanning the monadic arguments from left to right. For example, 
--  <pre>
--  
--      liftM2 (+) [0,1] [0,2] = [0,2,1,3]
--  </pre> 
--  <pre>
--  
--      liftM2 (+) (Just 1) Nothing = Nothing   
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#liftM2
liftM2 ∷ Monad β ⇒ (δ→γ→α) → β δ → β γ → β α

-- | Promote a function to a monad, scanning the monadic arguments from left to right (cf. <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#liftM2" >liftM2</a>).
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#liftM3
liftM3 ∷ Monad δ ⇒ (γ→α→β→ε) → δ γ → δ α → δ β → δ ε

-- | Promote a function to a monad, scanning the monadic arguments from left to right (cf. <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#liftM2" >liftM2</a>).
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#liftM4
liftM4 ∷ Monad α ⇒ (ε→ζ→γ→δ→β) → α ε → α ζ → α γ → α δ → α β

-- | Promote a function to a monad, scanning the monadic arguments from left to right (cf. <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#liftM2" >liftM2</a>).
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#liftM5
liftM5 ∷ Monad η ⇒ (α→β→δ→ε→γ→ζ) → η α → η β → η δ → η ε → η γ → η ζ

-- | The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#mapAndUnzipM" >mapAndUnzipM</a> function maps its first argument over a list, returning the result as a pair of lists. This function is mainly used with complicated data structures or a state-transforming monad.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#mapAndUnzipM
mapAndUnzipM ∷ Monad α ⇒ (β→α (δ, γ)) → [β] → α ([δ], [γ])

-- | The <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#zipWithM" >zipWithM</a> function generalizes <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeList.html#zipWith" >zipWith</a> to arbitrary monads.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#zipWithM
zipWithM ∷ Monad γ ⇒ (α→β→γ δ) → [α] → [β] → γ [δ]

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#zipWithM_" >zipWithM_</a> is the extension of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#zipWithM" >zipWithM</a> which ignores the final result.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#zipWithM_
zipWithM_ ∷ Monad δ ⇒ (β→α→δ γ) → [β] → [α] → δ ()

-- | Turn a list of monadic values <span class="code" >[m a]</span> into a monadic value with a list <span class="code" >m [a]</span> 
--  <pre>
--  
--   sequence [Just 1, Just 3, Just 2] = Just [1,2,3]
--  </pre> 
--   This version of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#sequence" >sequence</a> runs in constant stack space, but needs heap space proportional to the size of the input list.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#sequence
sequence ∷ Monad β ⇒ [β α] → β [α]

-- | A version of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#sequence" >sequence</a> that uses the stack and may overflow with longer lists. 
--   A length of about 500 should be ok in most cases.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#shortSequence
shortSequence ∷ Monad α ⇒ [α β] → α [β]

-- | fold (<a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad._gt_gt" >Monad.>></a>) over a list of monadic values for side effects
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#sequence_
sequence_ ∷ Monad α ⇒ [α β] → α ()

-- | <span class="code" >mapM f</span> is equivalent to <span class="code" >sequence • map f</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#mapM
mapM ∷ Monad β ⇒ (γ→β α) → [γ] → β [α]

-- | <span class="code" >mapM_ f</span> is equivalent to <span class="code" >sequence_ • map f</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#mapM_
mapM_ ∷ Monad β ⇒ (γ→β α) → [γ] → β ()

-- | <span class="code" >forM xs f</span> = <span class="code" >mapM_ f xs</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#forM
forM ∷ Monad β ⇒ [α] → (α→β γ) → β [γ]

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#forM_
forM_ ∷ Monad α ⇒ [β] → (β→α γ) → α ()

-- | <span class="code" >for listSource f</span> is a Java-friendly alias for <span class="code" >forM_</span> that works on any list source
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#_for
for ∷ (Monad m, ListSource listSource) ⇒ listSource e → (e → m a) → m ()

-- | <span class="code" >foldM f a xs</span> folds a monadic function <i >f</i> over the list <i >xs</i>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#foldM
foldM ∷ Monad α ⇒ (β→γ→α β) → β → [γ] → α β

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#shortFoldM" >shortFoldM</a> is suitable only for lists with a length way below 1000. 
--   Beware of stack overflow and use <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#foldM" >foldM</a> instead.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#shortFoldM
shortFoldM ∷ Monad β ⇒ (γ→α→β γ) → γ → [α] → β γ

-- | <span class="code" >foldM_</span> is the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#foldM" >foldM</a>, but discards the result
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#foldM_
foldM_ ∷ Monad β ⇒ (γ→α→β γ) → γ → [α] → β ()

-- | <span class="code" >guard b</span> is <span class="code" >return ()</span> if <span class="code" >b</span> is <b ><span class="code" >true</span></b>, and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#MonadZero.mzero" >MonadZero.mzero</a> otherwise.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#guard
guard ∷ MonadZero α ⇒ Bool → α ()

-- | <span class="code" >when condition monadic</span> returns /action/ of type <span class="code" >Monad m => m ()</span> if /condition/ is true, otherwise <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Monad._return" >Monad.return</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#Unit" >()</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#when
when ∷ Monad α ⇒ Bool → α () → α ()

-- | opposite of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#when" >when</a>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#unless
unless ∷ Monad α ⇒ Bool → α () → α ()

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#Reader
type Reader = ->

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#runReader
runReader ∷ (r → a) → r → a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#mapReader
mapReader ∷ (a → b) → (r → a) → r → b

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeMonad#withReader
withReader ∷ (e → r) → (r → a) → e → a

-- | Classes and Instances to convert values to <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a>s (<a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>) and <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a>s to values ("read").
--   There are a few differences to Haskell, notably<ul > <li > "Read" cannot be derived and supports only simple types </li> </ul>
module frege.prelude.PreludeText

-- | Haskell compatibility
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#ShowS
type ShowS = StringJ Char → StringJ Char

-- | Haskell compatibility
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#ReadS
type ReadS a = StringJ Char → [(a, StringJ Char)]

-- | Class <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a> provides operations to convert values to <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a>s. 
--   This class can be derived for all algebraic data types whose constituents are themselves instances of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a>. <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Bool" >Bool</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_l__r" >()</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_l_c_r" >(,)</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_l_cc_r" >(,,)</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Int" >Int</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Char" >Char</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Byte" >Lang.Byte</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Either" >Either</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Double" >Double</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Float" >Float</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_String" >StringJ</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Ordering" >Ordering</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Long" >Long</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Integer" >Integer</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Maybe" >Maybe</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Short" >Lang.Short</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Regex" >Regex</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show__lbrack_rbrack" >[]</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show_Throwable" >Throwable</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Show.display" >display</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a> show ⇒ show → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a></span> 
--   
--   <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.display" >Show.display</a> computes an alternate string representation of a value and is used in the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#Char" >Char</a> and <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> instances of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a> to produce an unquoted string. 
--   The default implementation is to do the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>.  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Show.show" >show</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a> show ⇒ show → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a></span> 
--   
--   Computes the string representation of a value. 
--   Every instance must implement <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Show.showChars" >showChars</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a> show ⇒ show → [<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#Char" >Char</a>]</span> 
--   
--   <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showChars" >Show.showChars</a> addresses the problem of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>ing infinite values. Because <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a> has type <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> and <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> is atomic, this would try to create a string with infinite length, and hence is doomed to fail. 
--   The default definition is 
--  <pre>
--  
--   showChars = String.toList . show
--  </pre> 
--   This is ok for all finite values. But instances for recursive types should implement it in a way that produces a lazy list of characters. 
--   Here is an example for the list instance: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   showChars [] = ['[', ']']
--   showChars xs = '[' : ( tail [ c | x &lt;- xs, c &lt;- ',' : showChars x ] ++ [']'] )
--  </pre>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Show.showList" >showList</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a> show ⇒ <b >[show]</b> → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a></span> 
--   
--   Haskell compatibility   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Show.showsPrec" >showsPrec</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a> show ⇒ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a> → show → <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a></span> 
--   
--   Haskell compatibility   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Show.showsub" >showsub</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a> show ⇒ show → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a></span> 
--   
--   <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showsub" >Show.showsub</a> is used for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>ing elements of a value of an algebraic data type in derived instances of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a>. 
--   The generated code in derived instances for types that are not enumerations is 
--  <pre>
--  
--   showsub x = &quot;(&quot; ++ show x ++ &quot;)&quot;
--  </pre> 
--   so that values are enclosed in parentheses. Certain types like records, lists, tuples and many primitive types do not need extra parentheses, and thus <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showsub" >Show.showsub</a> is the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>, which is also the default implementation. 
--   In short, <ul > <li > in derived instances, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showsub" >Show.showsub</a> will do the right thing. </li> <li > in all other instances, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showsub" >Show.showsub</a> will do the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a> if not implemented differently.</li> </ul> 
--   Example: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   derive Show ( Maybe b)
--  </pre> 
--   implements the following: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   show Nothing = &quot;Nothing&quot;
--   show (Just x) = &quot;Just &quot; ++ x.showsub
--   showsub x = &quot;(&quot; ++ show x ++ &quot;)&quot;
--  </pre> 
--   so that 
--  <pre>
--  
--   show (Just (Just 42)) == &quot;Just (Just 42)&quot;
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show
class Show show

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.display" >Show.display</a> computes an alternate string representation of a value and is used in the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#Char" >Char</a> and <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> instances of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a> to produce an unquoted string. 
--   The default implementation is to do the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.display
display ∷ Show show ⇒ show → String

-- | Computes the string representation of a value. 
--   Every instance must implement <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show
show ∷ Show show ⇒ show → String

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showChars" >Show.showChars</a> addresses the problem of <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>ing infinite values. Because <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a> has type <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> and <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> is atomic, this would try to create a string with infinite length, and hence is doomed to fail. 
--   The default definition is 
--  <pre>
--  
--   showChars = String.toList . show
--  </pre> 
--   This is ok for all finite values. But instances for recursive types should implement it in a way that produces a lazy list of characters. 
--   Here is an example for the list instance: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   showChars [] = ['[', ']']
--   showChars xs = '[' : ( tail [ c | x &lt;- xs, c &lt;- ',' : showChars x ] ++ [']'] )
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showChars
showChars ∷ Show show ⇒ show → [Char]

-- | Haskell compatibility
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showList
showList ∷ Show show ⇒ [show] → String → String

-- | Haskell compatibility
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showsPrec
showsPrec ∷ Show show ⇒ Int → show → String → String

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showsub" >Show.showsub</a> is used for <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>ing elements of a value of an algebraic data type in derived instances of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show" >Show</a>. 
--   The generated code in derived instances for types that are not enumerations is 
--  <pre>
--  
--   showsub x = &quot;(&quot; ++ show x ++ &quot;)&quot;
--  </pre> 
--   so that values are enclosed in parentheses. Certain types like records, lists, tuples and many primitive types do not need extra parentheses, and thus <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showsub" >Show.showsub</a> is the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a>, which is also the default implementation. 
--   In short, <ul > <li > in derived instances, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showsub" >Show.showsub</a> will do the right thing. </li> <li > in all other instances, <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showsub" >Show.showsub</a> will do the same as <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.show" >Show.show</a> if not implemented differently.</li> </ul> 
--   Example: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   derive Show ( Maybe b)
--  </pre> 
--   implements the following: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   show Nothing = &quot;Nothing&quot;
--   show (Just x) = &quot;Just &quot; ++ x.showsub
--   showsub x = &quot;(&quot; ++ show x ++ &quot;)&quot;
--  </pre> 
--   so that 
--  <pre>
--  
--   show (Just (Just 42)) == &quot;Just (Just 42)&quot;
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#Show.showsub
showsub ∷ Show show ⇒ show → String

-- | <span class="code" >joined sep xs</span> concatenates all strings in /xs/, and inserts /sep/ between any two elements of /xs/. 
--   If /xs/ is empty, the result is an empty string. If /sep/ is an empty string, then the result is just the concatenation of the strings in /xs/. 
--   Example: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   joined &quot;, &quot; [&quot;aaa&quot;, &quot;bbb&quot;, &quot;ccc&quot;] == &quot;aaa, bbb, ccc&quot;
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#joined
joined ∷ String → [String] → String

-- | convert a list of characters to a string 
--  <pre>
--  
--   packed ['a', 'b', 'c' ] == &quot;abc&quot;
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#packed
packed ∷ [Char] → String

-- | Haskell compatibility
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#shows
shows ∷ Show a ⇒ a → String → String

-- | Haskell compatibility
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#showChar
showChar ∷ Char → String → String

-- | Haskell compatibility
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#showString
showString ∷ String → String → String

-- | Haskell compatibility
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#showParen
showParen ∷ Bool → (String → String) → String → String

-- | splits a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> on end-of-line and returns a list of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a>s 
--   The last line may or may not be terminated by newline. 
--   End-of-line is signaled by a number of carriage returns followed by a new line. 
--   This should work for UNIX and Windows.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#lines
lines ∷ String → [String]

-- | The line separator suitable for the platform the program is running on.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#lineSeparator
lineSeparator ∷ String

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#unlines" >unlines</a> is an inverse operation to <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#lines" >lines</a>. 
--   It joins lines, after appending a terminating newline to each.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#unlines
unlines ∷ [String] → String

-- | strip trailing spaces, tabs, newline and carriage return characters from a string
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#chomp
chomp ∷ String → String

-- | splits a <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a> on non empty sequences of spaces and returns a list of <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/./PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a>s
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#words
words ∷ String → [String]

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#unwords" >unwords</a> is an inverse operation to <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#words" >words</a>. 
--   It joins words with separating spaces.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/prelude/PreludeText#unwords
unwords ∷ [String] → String

-- | Public interface for the quick check modules
module frege.test.QuickCheck

module frege.test.QuickCheckArbitrary

-- | class Arbitrary 
--   Random generation and shrinking of values. 
--   Minimal complete definition: <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary.arbitrary" >Arbitrary.arbitrary</a>  <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary__minus_gt" >-></a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_l_cc_r" >(,,)</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_l__r" >()</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_l_c_r" >(,)</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_l_ccc_r" >(,,,)</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_l_cccc_r" >(,,,,)</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Maybe" >Maybe</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Either" >Either</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Byte" >Lang.Byte</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Bool" >Bool</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Char" >Char</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Double" >Double</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Integer" >Integer</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Int" >Int</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Float" >Float</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_JArray" >JArray</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Long" >Long</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_TreeMap" >TM.TreeMap</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Short" >Lang.Short</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_Ordering" >Ordering</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary_String" >StringJ</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary__lbrack_rbrack" >[]</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Arbitrary.arbitrary" >arbitrary</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary" >Arbitrary</a> a ⇒ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/./QuickCheckGen.html#Gen" >Gen</a> a</span> 
--   
--   A generator for values of the given type.   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Arbitrary.shrink" >shrink</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary" >Arbitrary</a> a ⇒ a → [a]</span> 
--   
--   Produces a (possibly) empty list of all the possible immediate shrinks of the given value.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary
class Arbitrary a

-- | A generator for values of the given type.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary.arbitrary
arbitrary ∷ Arbitrary a ⇒ Gen a

-- | Produces a (possibly) empty list of all the possible immediate shrinks of the given value.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#Arbitrary.shrink
shrink ∷ Arbitrary a ⇒ a → [a]

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#shrinkList
shrinkList ∷ (a → [a]) → [a] → [[a]]

-- | Generates an integral number. The number can be positive or negative and its maximum absolute value depends on the size parameter.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#arbitrarySizedIntegral
arbitrarySizedIntegral ∷ Num a ⇒ Gen a

-- | Generates a fractional number. The number can be positive or negative and its maximum absolute value depends on the size parameter.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#arbitrarySizedFloating
arbitrarySizedFloating ∷ Floating a ⇒ Gen a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#arbitraryBoundedIntegral
arbitraryBoundedIntegral ∷ (Bounded a, Integral a) ⇒ Gen a

-- | Generates an element of a bounded type. The element is chosen from the entire range of the type.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#arbitraryBoundedRandom
arbitraryBoundedRandom ∷ (Bounded a, Random a) ⇒ Gen a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#arbitraryBoundedEnum
arbitraryBoundedEnum ∷ (Bounded a, Enum a) ⇒ Gen a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#arbitrarySizedBoundedIntegral
arbitrarySizedBoundedIntegral ∷ (Bounded a, Integral a) ⇒ Gen a

-- | Returns no shrinking alternatives.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#shrinkNothing
shrinkNothing ∷ a → [a]

-- | Shrink an integral number.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#shrinkIntegral
shrinkIntegral ∷ Integral a ⇒ a → [a]

-- | Shrink a fraction.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#shrinkFloating
shrinkFloating ∷ Floating a ⇒ a → [a]

-- | CoArbitrary 
--   Used for random generation of functions.  <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary__minus_gt" >-></a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_l_c_r" >(,)</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_l__r" >()</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_l_ccc_r" >(,,,)</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_l_cc_r" >(,,)</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_l_cccc_r" >(,,,,)</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_Ordering" >Ordering</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_Integer" >Integer</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_Either" >Either</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_Char" >Long</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_TreeMap" >TM.TreeMap</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary_String" >StringJ</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary__lbrack_rbrack" >[]</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="CoArbitrary.coarbitrary" >coarbitrary</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary" >CoArbitrary</a> a ⇒ a → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/./QuickCheckGen.html#Gen" >Gen</a> c → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/./QuickCheckGen.html#Gen" >Gen</a> c</span> 
--   
--   Used to generate a function of type <span class="code" >a -> c</span>. The implementation should use the first argument to perturb the random generator given as the second argument. The returned generator is then used to generate the function result. 
--   You can often use <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/./QuickCheckGen.html#variant" >QuickCheckGen.variant</a> and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#_gt_lt" >><</a> to implement <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary.coarbitrary" >CoArbitrary.coarbitrary</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary
class CoArbitrary a

-- | Used to generate a function of type <span class="code" >a -> c</span>. The implementation should use the first argument to perturb the random generator given as the second argument. The returned generator is then used to generate the function result. 
--   You can often use <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/./QuickCheckGen.html#variant" >QuickCheckGen.variant</a> and <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#_gt_lt" >><</a> to implement <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary.coarbitrary" >CoArbitrary.coarbitrary</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary.coarbitrary
coarbitrary ∷ CoArbitrary a ⇒ a → Gen c → Gen c

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#_gt_lt
(><) ∷  (Gen a → Gen a) → (Gen a → Gen a) → Gen a → Gen a 
infixr  1

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#coarbitraryIntegral
coarbitraryIntegral ∷ Integral a ⇒ a → Gen b → Gen b

-- | <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary.coarbitrary" >CoArbitrary.coarbitrary</a> helper for lazy people :-).
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#coarbitraryShow
coarbitraryShow ∷ Show a ⇒ a → Gen b → Gen b

-- | A <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#CoArbitrary.coarbitrary" >CoArbitrary.coarbitrary</a> implementation for enums.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#coarbitraryEnum
coarbitraryEnum ∷ Enum a ⇒ a → Gen b → Gen b

-- | <ul > <li > ---------------------------------------------------------------------- </li> </ul> 
--   Generates a list of a given length.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#vector
vector ∷ Arbitrary a ⇒ Int → Gen [a]

-- | Generates an ordered list of a given length.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckArbitrary#orderedList
orderedList ∷ (Ord a, Arbitrary a) ⇒ Gen [a]

module frege.test.QuickCheckException

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckException#AnException
type AnException = Exception

-- | <ul > <li > ---------------------------------------------------------------------- </li> </ul>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckException#tryEvaluate
tryEvaluate ∷ a → IO (Exception | a)

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckException#tryEvaluateIO
tryEvaluateIO ∷ IO a → IO (Exception | a)

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckException#isInterrupt
isInterrupt ∷ Exception → Bool

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckException#discard
discard ∷ a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckException#isDiscard

-- | Test case generation.
module frege.test.QuickCheckGen

-- | Generator type  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Gen.MkGen" >MkGen</a> {unGen ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../system/Random.html#StdGen" >StdGen</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a> → a}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Gen.unGen" >unGen</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#Gen" >Gen</a> α</b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../system/Random.html#StdGen" >StdGen</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a> → α</span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >unGen</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#Gen
data Gen a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#Gen.MkGen
MkGen {unGen ∷ StdGen → Int → a}

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#variant
variant ∷ Integral n ⇒ n → Gen a → Gen a

-- | Used to construct generators that depend on the size parameter.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#sized
sized ∷ (Int → Gen a) → Gen a

-- | Overrides the size parameter. Returns a generator which uses the given size instead of the runtime-size parameter.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#resize
resize ∷ Int → Gen a → Gen a

-- | Generates a random element in the given inclusive range.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#choose
choose ∷ Random a ⇒ (a, a) → Gen a

-- | Promotes a monadic generator to a generator of monadic values.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#promote
promote ∷ Monad m ⇒ m (Gen a) → Gen (m a)

-- | Generates some example values.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#sample_tick
sample' ∷ Gen a → IO [a]

-- | Generates some example values and prints them to <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../java/IO.html#stdout" >IO.stdout</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#sample
sample ∷ Show a ⇒ Gen a → IO ()

-- | Generates a value that satisfies a predicate.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#suchThat
suchThat ∷ Gen a → (a → Bool) → Gen a

-- | Tries to generate a value that satisfies a predicate.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#suchThatMaybe
suchThatMaybe ∷ Gen a → (a → Bool) → Gen (Maybe a)

-- | Randomly uses one of the given generators. The input list must be non-empty.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#oneof
oneof ∷ [Gen a] → Gen a

-- | Chooses one of the given generators, with a weighted random distribution. The input list must be non-empty.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#frequency
frequency ∷ [(Int, Gen a)] → Gen a

-- | Generates one of the given values. The input list must be non-empty.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#elements
elements ∷ [a] → Gen a

-- | Takes a list of elements of increasing size, and chooses among an initial segment of the list. The size of this initial segment increases with the size parameter. The input list must be non-empty.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#growingElements
growingElements ∷ [a] → Gen a

-- | Generates a list of random length. 
--   The maximum length depends on the size parameter.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#listOf
listOf ∷ Gen a → Gen [a]

-- | Generates a non-empty list of random length. 
--   The maximum length depends on the size parameter.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#listOf1
listOf1 ∷ Gen a → Gen [a]

-- | Generates a list of the given length.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckGen#vectorOf
vectorOf ∷ Int → Gen a → Gen [a]

-- | Modifiers for test data.
--   These types do things such as restricting the kind of test data that can be generated. They can be pattern-matched on in properties as a stylistic alternative to using explicit quantification.
--   Examples:
--  <pre>
--  
--   -- Functions cannot be shown (but see &quot;Test.QuickCheck.Function&quot;)
--   prop_TakeDropWhile (Blind p) (xs :: [A]) =
--    takeWhile p xs ++ dropWhile p xs == xs
--  </pre>
--  <pre>
--  
--   prop_TakeDrop ('NonNegative' n) (xs :: ['A']) =
--    take n xs ++ drop n xs == xs
--  </pre>
--  <pre>
--  
--   -- cycle does not work for empty lists
--   prop_Cycle ('NonNegative' n) ('NonEmpty' (xs :: ['A'])) =
--    take n (cycle xs) == take n (xs ++ cycle xs)
--  </pre>
--  <pre>
--  
--   -- Instead of 'forAll' 'orderedList'
--   prop_Sort ('Ordered' (xs :: ['OrdA'])) =
--     sort xs == xs
--  </pre>
module frege.test.QuickCheckModifiers

-- | <span class="code" >Blind x</span>: as x, but x does not have to be in the <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeText.html#Show" >Show</a> class.  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Blind.Blind" >Blind</a> a</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#Blind
data Blind a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#Blind.Blind
Blind a

-- | <span class="code" >Fixed x</span>: as x, but will not be shrunk.  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Fixed.Fixed" >Fixed</a> a</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#Fixed
data Fixed a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#Fixed.Fixed
Fixed a

-- | <span class="code" >Ordered xs</span>: guarantees that xs is ordered.  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="OrderedList.Ordered" >Ordered</a> {getOrdered ∷ [a]}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="OrderedList.getOrdered" >getOrdered</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#OrderedList" >OrderedList</a> α</b> → [α]</span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >getOrdered</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#OrderedList
data OrderedList a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#OrderedList.Ordered
Ordered {getOrdered ∷ [a]}

-- | <span class="code" >NonEmpty xs</span>: guarantees that xs is non-empty.  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="NonEmptyList.NonEmpty" >NonEmpty</a> {getNonEmpty ∷ [a]}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="NonEmptyList.getNonEmpty" >getNonEmpty</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#NonEmptyList" >NonEmptyList</a> α</b> → [α]</span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >getNonEmpty</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#NonEmptyList
data NonEmptyList a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#NonEmptyList.NonEmpty
NonEmpty {getNonEmpty ∷ [a]}

-- | <span class="code" >Positive x</span>: guarantees that <span class="code" >x > 0</span>.  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Positive.Positive" >Positive</a> {getPositive ∷ a}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Positive.getPositive" >getPositive</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#Positive" >Positive</a> α</b> → α</span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >getPositive</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#Positive
data Positive a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#Positive.Positive
Positive {getPositive ∷ a}

-- | <span class="code" >NonZero x</span>: guarantees that <span class="code" >x != 0</span>.  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="NonZero.NonZero" >NonZero</a> {getNonZero ∷ a}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="NonZero.getNonZero" >getNonZero</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#NonZero" >NonZero</a> α</b> → α</span>

--   access field <span class="code" >getNonZero</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#NonZero
data NonZero a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#NonZero.NonZero
NonZero {getNonZero ∷ a}

-- | <span class="code" >NonNegative x</span>: guarantees that <span class="code" >x >= 0</span>.  <h3 > Constructors</h3>

--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>

--   access field <span class="code" >getNonNegative</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckModifiers#NonNegative
data NonNegative a

NonNegative {getNonNegative ∷ a}

module frege.test.QuickCheckProperty

-- | The things quick check is testing
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Property
type Property = Gen Prop

-- | The class of things which can be tested, i.e. turned into a property.  <h3 > Known Instances</h3> 
--   <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Testable_Bool" >Bool</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Testable__minus_gt" >-></a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Testable_Result" >Result</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Testable_Prop" >Prop</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Testable_Gen" >QuickCheckGen.Gen</a> <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Testable.exhaustive" >exhaustive</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Testable" >Testable</a> prop ⇒ prop → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a></span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Testable.property" >property</a> ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Testable" >Testable</a> prop ⇒ prop → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Property" >Property</a></span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Testable
class Testable prop

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Testable.exhaustive
exhaustive ∷ Testable prop ⇒ prop → Bool

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Testable.property
property ∷ Testable prop ⇒ prop → Property

-- | Do I/O inside a property. This can obviously lead to unrepeatable testcases, so use with care.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#morallyDubiousIOProperty
morallyDubiousIOProperty ∷ Testable prop ⇒ IO prop → Property

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#protect
protect ∷ (Exception → a) → IO a → IO a

-- | <ul > <li > ---------------------------------------------------------------------- </li> </ul> <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Prop.MkProp" >MkProp</a> {unProp ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Rose" >Rose</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result" >Result</a>}</span> 
--     <h3 > Member Functions</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Prop.unProp" >unProp</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Prop" >Prop</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Rose" >Rose</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result" >Result</a></span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >unProp</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Prop
data Prop

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Prop.MkProp
MkProp {unProp ∷ Rose Result}

-- | <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Rose.IORose" >IORose</a> (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Rose" >Rose</a> a))</span> 
--    
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Rose.MkRose" >MkRose</a> a   [<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Rose" >Rose</a> a]</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Rose
data Rose a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Rose.IORose
IORose (IO (Rose a))

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Rose.MkRose
MkRose a   [Rose a]

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#ioRose
ioRose ∷ IO (Rose Result) → Rose Result

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#joinRose
joinRose ∷ Rose (Rose a) → Rose a

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#reduceRose
reduceRose ∷ Rose Result → IO (Rose Result)

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#onRose
onRose ∷ (a → [Rose a] → Rose a) → Rose a → Rose a

-- | Wrap a rose tree in an exception handler.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#protectRose
protectRose ∷ IO (Rose Result) → IO (Rose Result)

-- | Wrap all the Results in a rose tree in exception handlers.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#protectResults
protectResults ∷ Rose Result → Rose Result

-- | Different kinds of callbacks  <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Callback.PostFinalFailure" >PostFinalFailure</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#CallbackKind" >CallbackKind</a>   (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/./QuickCheckState.html#State" >State</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result" >Result</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Unit" >()</a>)</span> 
--   
--   Called with the final failing test-case   
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Callback.PostTest" >PostTest</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#CallbackKind" >CallbackKind</a>   (<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/./QuickCheckState.html#State" >State</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result" >Result</a> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Unit" >()</a>)</span> 
--   
--   Called just after a test
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Callback
data Callback

-- | Called with the final failing test-case
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Callback.PostFinalFailure
PostFinalFailure CallbackKind   (State → Result → IO ())

-- | Called just after a test
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Callback.PostTest
PostTest CallbackKind   (State → Result → IO ())

-- | <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="CallbackKind.Counterexample" >Counterexample</a> </span>

--   
--   Not affected by the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#verbose" >verbose</a> combinator
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#CallbackKind
data CallbackKind

-- | Affected by the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#verbose" >verbose</a> combinator
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#CallbackKind.Counterexample
Counterexample

-- | Not affected by the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#verbose" >verbose</a> combinator
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#CallbackKind.NotCounterexample
NotCounterexample

-- | <h3 > Constructors</h3>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Result.MkResult" >MkResult</a> {ok ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Maybe" >Maybe</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a>, expect ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a>, reason ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a>, interrupted ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a>, abort ∷ <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a>, stamp ∷ [(<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a>)], callbacks ∷ [<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Callback" >Callback</a>]}</span>

--   
--   access field <span class="code" >callbacks</span>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Result.expect" >expect</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result" >Result</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a></span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >expect</span>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Result.interrupted" >interrupted</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result" >Result</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a></span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >interrupted</span>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Result.ok" >ok</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result" >Result</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Maybe" >Maybe</a> <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Bool" >Bool</a></span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >ok</span>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Result.reason" >reason</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result" >Result</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a></span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >reason</span>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="Result.stamp" >stamp</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result" >Result</a></b> → [(<a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#String" >String</a>, <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a>)]</span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >stamp</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result
data Result

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#Result.MkResult
MkResult {ok ∷ Maybe Bool, expect ∷ Bool, reason ∷ String, interrupted ∷ Bool, abort ∷ Bool, stamp ∷ [(String, Int)], callbacks ∷ [Callback]}

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#result
result ∷ Result

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#exception
exception ∷ String → Exception → Result

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#formatException
formatException ∷ String → Exception → String

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#protectResult
protectResult ∷ IO Result → IO Result

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#succeeded
succeeded ∷ Result

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#failed
failed ∷ Result

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#rejected
rejected ∷ Result

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#liftBool
liftBool ∷ Bool → Result

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#mapResult
mapResult ∷ Testable prop ⇒ (Result → Result) → prop → Property

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#mapTotalResult
mapTotalResult ∷ Testable prop ⇒ (Result → Result) → prop → Property

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#mapRoseResult
mapRoseResult ∷ Testable prop ⇒ (Rose Result → Rose Result) → prop → Property

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#mapProp
mapProp ∷ Testable prop ⇒ (Prop → Prop) → prop → Property

-- | Changes the maximum test case size for a property.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#mapSize
mapSize ∷ Testable prop ⇒ (Int → Int) → prop → Property

-- | Shrinks the argument to property if it fails. Shrinking is done automatically for most types. This is only needed when you want to override the default behavior.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#shrinking
shrinking ∷ Testable prop ⇒ (a → [a]) → a → (a → prop) → Property

-- | Disables shrinking for a property altogether.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#noShrinking
noShrinking ∷ Testable prop ⇒ prop → Property

-- | Adds a callback
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#callback
callback ∷ Testable prop ⇒ Callback → prop → Property

-- | Prints a message to the terminal as part of the counterexample.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#printTestCase
printTestCase ∷ Testable prop ⇒ String → prop → Property

-- | Performs an <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#IO" >IO</a> action after the last failure of a property.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#whenFail
whenFail ∷ Testable prop ⇒ IO () → prop → Property

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#whenFail_tick
whenFail' ∷ Testable prop ⇒ IO () → prop → Property

-- | Prints out the generated testcase every time the property is tested, like "verboseCheck" from QuickCheck 1. Only variables quantified over <i >inside</i> the <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#verbose" >verbose</a> are printed.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#verbose
verbose ∷ Testable prop ⇒ prop → Property

-- | Modifies a property so that it is expected to fail for some test cases.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#expectFailure
expectFailure ∷ Testable prop ⇒ prop → Property

-- | Modifies a property so that it only will be tested once.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#once
once ∷ Testable prop ⇒ prop → Property

-- | Attaches a label to a property. 
--   This is used for reporting test case distribution.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#label
label ∷ Testable prop ⇒ String → prop → Property

-- | Labels a property with a value: 
--  <pre>
--  
--   collect x = label (show x)   
--  </pre>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#collect
collect ∷ (Show a, Testable prop) ⇒ a → prop → Property

-- | Conditionally labels test case.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#classify
classify ∷ Testable prop ⇒ Bool → String → prop → Property

-- | Checks that at least the given proportion of the test cases belong to the given class.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#cover
cover ∷ Testable prop ⇒ Bool → Int → String → prop → Property

-- | Implication for properties: The resulting property holds if the first argument is <span class="code" >false</span> (in which case the test case is discarded), or if the given property holds.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#_eq_eq_gt
(==>) ∷  Testable prop ⇒ Bool → prop → Property 
infixr  1

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#within
within ∷ Testable prop ⇒ Int → prop → Property

-- | Explicit universal quantification: uses an explicitly given test case generator.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#forAll
forAll ∷ (Show a, Testable prop) ⇒ Gen a → (a → prop) → Property

-- | Like <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#forAll" >forAll</a>, but tries to shrink the argument for failing test cases.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#forAllShrink
forAllShrink ∷ (Show a, Testable prop) ⇒ Gen a → (a → [a]) → (a → prop) → Property

-- | Nondeterministic choice: <span class="code" >p1 .&. p2</span> picks randomly one of <span class="code" >p1</span> and <span class="code" >p2</span> to test. If you test the property 100 times it makes 100 random choices.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#_dot_amp_dot
(.&.) ∷  (Testable prop1, Testable prop2) ⇒ prop1 → prop2 → Property 
infixr  2

-- | Conjunction: <span class="code" >p1 .&&. p2</span> passes if both <span class="code" >p1</span> and <span class="code" >p2</span> pass.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#_dot_amp_amp_dot
(.&&.) ∷  (Testable prop1, Testable prop2) ⇒ prop1 → prop2 → Property 
infixr  2

-- | Take the conjunction of several properties.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#conjoin
conjoin ∷ Testable prop ⇒ [prop] → Property

-- | Disjunction: <span class="code" >p1 .||. p2</span> passes unless <span class="code" >p1</span> and <span class="code" >p2</span> simultaneously fail.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#_dot_bar_bar_dot
(.||.) ∷  (Testable prop1, Testable prop2) ⇒ prop1 → prop2 → Property 
infixr  2

-- | Take the disjunction of several properties.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckProperty#disjoin
disjoin ∷ Testable prop ⇒ [prop] → Property

--   <span class="code" ><a name="State.numTotTryShrinks" >numTotTryShrinks</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckState#State" >State</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >numTotTryShrinks</span>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="State.numTryShrinks" >numTryShrinks</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckState#State" >State</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../prelude/PreludeBase.html#Int" >Int</a></span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >numTryShrinks</span>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="State.randomSeed" >randomSeed</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckState#State" >State</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../system/Random.html#StdGen" >StdGen</a></span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >randomSeed</span>  
--   <span class="code" ><a name="State.terminal" >terminal</a> ∷ <b ><a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckState#State" >State</a></b> → <a class="tref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/./QuickCheckText.html#Terminal" >Terminal</a></span> 
--   
--   access field <span class="code" >terminal</span>
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckState#State
data State

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckState#State.MkState
MkState {terminal ∷ Terminal, maxSuccessTests ∷ Int, maxDiscardedTests ∷ Int, computeSize ∷ Int → Int → Int, numSuccessTests ∷ Int, numDiscardedTests ∷ Int, numRecentlyDiscardedTests ∷ Int, collected ∷ [[(String, Int)]], expectedFailure ∷ Bool, randomSeed ∷ StdGen, numSuccessShrinks ∷ Int, numTryShrinks ∷ Int, numTotTryShrinks ∷ Int}

--   maximum number of successful tests before succeeding

--   
--   should we replay a previous test?

data Result

Failure {numTests ∷ Int, numShrinks ∷ Int, usedSeed ∷ StdGen, usedSize ∷ Int, reason ∷ String, interrupted ∷ Bool, labels ∷ [(String, Int)], output ∷ String}

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckTest#Result.Success

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckTest#isSuccess
isSuccess ∷ Result → Bool

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckTest#stdArgs

@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckTest#quickCheck
quickCheck ∷ Testable prop ⇒ prop → IO ()

-- | Tests a property, using test arguments, and prints the results to <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../java/IO.html#stdout" >IO.stdout</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckTest#quickCheckWith
quickCheckWith ∷ Testable prop ⇒ Args → prop → IO ()

-- | Tests a property, produces a test result, and prints the results to <a class="fref" href="http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/../java/IO.html#stdout" >IO.stdout</a>.
@url http://www.frege-lang.org/doc/frege/test/QuickCheckTest#quickCheckResult
quickCheckResult ∷ Testable prop ⇒ prop → IO Result
